title: pizza dough
directions: Put together the first 3 ingredients.
In a large bowl, mix the oil, salt and wheat flour.
Knead by hand 6 to 7 minutes, adding white flour a little at a time.
Put in a greased bowl and cover. Leave in a warm place to rise 2 to 3 hours, until tripled.
Punch down and roll out some on lightly floured surface until thin.
This may be used for pizza and topped with sauce, cheese and veggies or for a calzone.

title: lobster-macaroni salad
directions: Thaw and pick lobster.
Squeeze lemon juice over lobster meat. Then add onion and celery.
Marinate 4 hours.

title: christmas mud squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stirring well. Press crumb mixture into bottom of a greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes; cool slightly. Combine caramel and 3 tablespoons flour, stirring well. Spread topping on crust to within 1/4-inch from edge. Set aside.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: This must be made the night before and refrigerated.

title: gourmet crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large mixing bowl by blending lightly, adding crab meat last.
Do not break crabmeat lumps.
Shape into 12 (2 1/2-inch) cakes.
Add extra bread crumbs to hold cakes together, if needed.
Place cake on buttered baking sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with lemon wedges and cocktail sauce.
Serves 6.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Put in a roll and freeze overnight.
Bake at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef and water for about 30 minutes, then add tomato juice.
Then add chili stick or block (chopped up) and let melt.
Then add chili beans.
Add onion.
Stir and cook about 30 minutes.

title: marinated italian salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water and 1/4 cup Italian dressing for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine rest of vegetables and 3/4 cup Italian dressing in large glass bowl.
Let stand at room temperature at least 2 hours, turning frequently.
Add mayo and blend. Refrigerate.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: In a well-buttered 2-quart casserole, arrange in alternate layers potatoes, onion and salt and pepper.
Repeat 3 times.
In small saucepan, heat soup with milk.
Pour over potato mixture. Cover and bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil margarine and water.
Cool 2 minutes; add flour.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a frying pan and pour off grease.
Add chopped onion, garlic, celery and green pepper to sausage.
Simmer until tender.
Wash rice and add mixture in Pyrex baking dish along with the soups.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add the other ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Put in greased pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk and eggs.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Remove core and seeds
from
pepper
and
cut
into 3/4-inch cubes.
Core tomatoes and
cut
into
1-inch pieces.
Coarsely chop onion. Peel and finely
chop garlic.
Put oil in 14-inch Dutch oven. Add all vegetables except tomatoes.
Stir and cook until onion becomes clear.
Add
rice
and
keep
stirring
until all the grains become
coated with oil.
Add tomatoes, broth, cayenne pepper and water.
Break up any clumps of rice.
Put oven over 14 coals until
mixture starts to boil.
Then put 12 coals on top and 10 coals on bottom.
Cook for 17 minutes.
Do not stir during this stage and do not remove lid.
Remove from heat and fluff with fork.
Put lid back on and let steam for 5 minutes.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Combine thoroughly and store in an airtight container.
To make hot chocolate, combine 1/3 cup mix and hot water in mug. Stir well.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients in the order listed.
Add lime zest.
Pour into pie crust; shape.
Add slices of lime to decorate.
Chill 2 hours.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Mix pudding, milk, condensed milk, vanilla flavoring and about 1/4 of Cool Whip together with a whisk. In a 2 qt. dish layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas, and pudding. Put in the refrigerator and let chill. Top with extra Cool Whip and for an extra look sprinkle with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: salmon fillets(serves 4)
directions: Rinse salmon.
Pat dry.
In flat, shallow dish, combine oil, mustard, lemon juice and shallots.
Roll salmon in mixture.
Coat both sides and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Place salmon on well oiled foil.
Place on grill about 4 to 6 inches from hot coals. Cook 10 to 12 minutes per inch of thickness or until flesh turns opaque and flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: spicy burgers with mushroom sauce
directions: Combine ground beef, soup mix, egg and Worcestershire sauce. Shape mixture into 6 patties.
Arrange patties on a microwave roasting rack placed in a 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove patties.
Pour off meat drippings from dish; return patties to dish.
Combine soup and 1/3 cup water; pour over patties.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave at Medium-high 5 to 7 minutes, or until sauce is bubbly hot.
Serve over toast or hot cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in baking dish. Combine sour cream and flour; mix well.
Add wine, soup, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix
together in bowl.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, allspice, cinnamon, soda and salt. Set aside.
Cream the sugar, oil, eggs (one at a time) and pumpkin.
Mix well all the ingredients. Bake in waxed paper lined pans at 350° until done.

title: pineapple custard
directions: Drain pineapple. Cook in 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix cornstarch in a little juice from the pineapple and add to pineapple.
Stir. Allow to thicken a little.
Spread the pineapple mixture on the bottom of glass dish (11 x 8-inch).
Separately mix the skim milk, dry milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Carefully pour over the pineapple.
Place glass dish in larger tray filled with water and place in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until top is slightly golden. Remove from oven. Cool in refrigerator.

title: plum nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend sugar, flour, spices and nuts. Add eggs, oil and baby food.
Beat until smooth.
Bake 1 hour.

title: cheesy bacon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Paper line 12 muffin cups.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, oats and bacon bits.
Combine egg, milk, oil and cheese.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar alternately with egg white, beating until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and food coloring. Makes 1 cup.

title: mile branch cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add egg, milk and lard. Stir until mixed.
Pour in greased iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine strawberries, Wesson oil and water.
Add strawberry Jell-O and cake mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well after each.
Bake in 3 layers at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: dough bowl biscuits
directions: Sift flour in bowl and make a well in center.
Take Crisco and start working it into flour gradually, adding buttermilk.
As you work the flour and Crisco, you may have to use a little more milk. When you have used all the milk, clean hands and then flour your hands well.
Knead about 4 times, then pinch a small amount off and roll in palm of hand.
Put in a greased pan and bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: Conventional:
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: orange cookie balls
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar; add nuts and vanilla wafers.
Blend well.
Add orange juice and blend well.
Roll into small balls, then in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Cool.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Add chocolate mixture and extract.
Add flour mixture, beating just until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a well-greased 9-inch square pan at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 25 brownies.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter; add both sugars.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips; let stand 5 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Knead with oiled hands until smooth.
Let raise 1 to 2 hours. Pound it down and divide into four loaves.
Use immediately or place each ball in a Ziploc bag.
(Put 1 teaspoon oil in each bag).
Refrigerate until ready to use.
It will last 2 weeks in the fridge.

title: spiced tea
directions: In a small bag, put 4 cinnamon sticks and about 20 cloves. Add to listed ingredients and simmer.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix with beaters until well mixed.
Pour into either a Bundt pan or an 11 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, depending on pan size.

title: golden rule gingerbread
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch square pan.
In a bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add the egg, sugar and molasses.
Mix well.
Pour the boiling water and oil over the mixture and stir until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until top springs back. Combine the confectioners sugar and lemon juice; pour over the hot gingerbread.
Cool in the pan on a wire rack.
Serves 12.

title: lemon herb marinated chicken
directions: In a cup, mix first five ingredients.
Pour over chicken. Cover and let stand at room temperature no longer than 30 minutes, turning once.
Broil 10 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, turning once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Put nuts and self-rising flour in a bowl by themselves. Combine all ingredients.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place cake in oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Take fork and test in middle of cake. If it doesn't stick, take out cake.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat oil in a large, heavy pot over medium heat.
Add chopped onion, garlic and chili pepper.
Saute until transparent, about 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, bell pepper, carrots, cumin, salt and cayenne.
Add 1 cup reserved juice.
Bring to a simmer. Cook 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add all of the beans and cook 15 minutes more, thinning with reserved juice if chili is too thick.
Add zucchini; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with grated cheese and chopped onion.

title: english muffin bread (microwave)(raisin cinnamon)
directions: In
a	large
bowl
combine
cups
flour,
raisins, undissolved
yeast,
sugar,
salt,	cinnamon
and baking soda. Combine milk
and
water; heat until very warm.
Gradually add to dry ingredients
and beat well.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon
into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) or (9 x 5-inch) loaf dishes, which have been greased and coated with cornmeal. Cover and let rise in a warm place for 45 minutes.

title: giant tostado
directions: Layer in order given and serve with the chips!

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, put in noodles, tuna, celery, green pepper and water chestnuts.
In a saucepan, combine celery soup and milk.
Heat, stirring, until smooth.
Add onions, mayonnaise, thyme, salt and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add sauce to casserole; mix gently and thoroughly.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and almonds.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly and slightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
(Can be halved for less servings.)

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, line with graham crackers. Mix pudding with milk, mix for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 the mixture over graham crackers.
Now place second layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour pudding mixture over the cracker and cover with more crackers.
(Three layers of crackers, 2 layers of filling.)
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In buttered baking dish, put a layer of asparagus and a layer of peas.
Sprinkle half of pimentos and eggs.
Repeat.
Pour warm soup over, then add grated cheese and crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marty's no roll pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: cream cheese chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan; line bottom and sides with aluminum foil.
Grease foil.
In a large mixing bowl of electric mixer, combine cookie mix, eggs, chocolate and baking powder; at low speed, beat until mixture forms a crumbly dough.
Pat dough over bottom of prepared pan; bake 20 minutes or until dough just begins to brown.
Remove pan from oven.

title: pineapple pic-ups
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple.
To 3/4 cup of syrup, add remaining ingredients.
Heat 10 minutes.
Add pineapple.
Bring to boil.
Refrigerate 2 days.
Serve ice cold (with toothpicks).

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Drain if needed. Stir in all other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: scotch shortbread(cookies)
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add brown sugar and cream well. Add flour until soft and dough is formed.
Separate dough into 2 or 3 logs.
Place in freezer until stiff enough to slice into 1-inch slices.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Best if dough is chilled before rolling into logs.

title: harvest stew
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain.
Drain all other ingredients and add; mix well and heat at least 30 minutes.

title: chocolate covered balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip candy into chocolate to coat.
Cool on waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: caramel refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix all together.
Form into a roll about 2 1/2-inches across.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Heat oven to 400°.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips and nuts, in large mixer bowl.
Blend well at lowest speed.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
No frosting needed.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Beat peanut butter and margarine until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Blend flour and salt into mixture.
Stir in 1 cup chips.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining chips and let stand 5 minutes, then spread melting chips over top and cut in squares.

title: fruit kabobs with yogurt dip
directions: On 6-inch wooden skewers, alternate pineapple, strawberries, bananas and kiwi fruit.
Combine yogurt and orange juice to make dip.
Cover and chill for 2 hours or longer.
Garnish with rind. Yields 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat.
Shred cabbage in a large pan.
Add meat, vegetables and juice.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
More juice or water can be added.
The longer it cooks, the better it tastes.
Before serving, bring to a boil and add soy sauce, bead molasses and sugar.
Take about 1/4 cup cornstarch, add some of the hot tomato juice to it and add to boiling mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel and
wash potatoes.
Put in pot and add all ingredients. Cook on low flame until mixture thickens.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together chopped pretzels, 1 tablespoon sugar and melted butter in a 13 x 9-inch dish and spread to form a crust.
Bake at 200° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Measure cereal and milk in
a large mixing bowl. Stir to moisten and soften a few minutes. Add egg and oil, mixing well. Add flour, powder, salt and sugar. Blend. Divide batter evenly in 12 greased muffin or cupcake pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: luck o'the irish quiche
directions: Mix corned beef hash, 1 egg and bread crumbs together well. Press into bottom of pie plate, sides and bottom.
Mix 3 eggs and milk well.
Lay cheese on top of corned beef in pie plate. Sprinkle cheese with flour.
Pour milk and egg mixture in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle Pepperidge Farm stuffing on top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add onion, milk and egg.
Fry teaspoonfuls of batter in hot fat until golden brown.
Drain; serve hot.

title: apple streusel mince pie
directions: In large bowl, toss apples with 3 tablespoons of flour and melted butter; arrange in pastry shell.
Top with mincemeat.
In medium bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup of flour, sugar and cinnamon; cut in cold butter until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Sprinkle over mincemeat.
Bake in lower half of 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 375°; bake 25 minutes longer or until golden.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Boil, then chop shrimp. Add ingredients with mayonnaise.
Keep refrigerated.

title: crab quiche
directions: Saute onions in butter 2 minutes.
Mix in crab, flour and spinach. Sprinkle half of the cheese in bottom of pie shell. Spread in crab/spinach mixture. Top with remaining cheese.
Beat eggs, cream, etc., until mixed but not frothy. Pour over pie. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: herb marinated chicken breasts(servings:  6)
directions: Stir together salad dressing, wine and seasonings.
Pour dressing mixture over chicken.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drain, reserving dressing mixture.
Place chicken on greased rack of broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 6 minutes on each side or until tender, brushing frequently with dressing mixture.
Calories: 170 each.
Fat:
7 grams.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Combine all cake ingredients in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly by hand.
Do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In medium
mixing
bowl,
combine all ingredients;
mix well. Shape into a
x 4-inch loaf.
Place in an 8 x 4-inch loaf dish. Microwave	at Medium-high for 15 to 20 minutes, or until beef is no	longer	pink,
rotating
dish
once.
Cover loosely with aluminum
foil.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Remove from dish.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine over low heat, stirring to prevent scorching.
Mix together sugar and cereal in a large bowl. Add peanut butter mixture and mix well.
Form into small balls with a teaspoon or fingers.
Place in freezer.

title: roger's perfect multigrain bread
directions: To be made in a bread machine.
Use white bread setting.
Use turbo setting or only knead and rise once.

title: fresh berry trifle
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package for pudding.
Cover surface of pudding with plastic wrap while cooling.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in flavoring.
Split ladyfingers lengthwise; arrange in a 2-quart glass serving bowl.
Line sides and bottom. Layer pudding, blueberries and remaining ladyfingers.
Beat whipping cream and brown sugar in chilled mixing bowl until stiff. Spread over trifle; sprinkle with almonds.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
To serve, spoon into dessert dishes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken broccoli 2
directions: In small bowl, combine chicken, soy sauce and vegetable oil. Place broccoli and 1/2 cup broth in wok or large skillet.
Cook 5 minutes; stir every minute.
Push to side.
Increase heat.
Add chicken mix and garlic; stir-fry 3 minutes and push to side.
Add mushrooms; stir-fry 1 minute.
Combine all ingredients in wok. Combine lemon juice and cornstarch with remaining 1/2 cup broth. Stir into wok mixture.
Heat 2 minutes; garnish with pimentos and sesame seed.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: philly beef stuffed sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Heat oil in skillet. Press garlic into hot oil, then add bell pepper, onion and half the oregano. Cook and stir until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat. Unroll one pizza crust and stretch into 9 x 13-inch rectangle. Cover with half the beef and cheese. Spread half the vegetable mixture over the cheese. Roll up jelly roll style, starting with the longer side of the rectangle. Place on pizza pan, seam side down in half circle. Repeat with other pizza crust and toppings, then place in pan to complete circle, joining ends by pinching together.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate.
It is better if refrigerated overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread undrained pineapple over bottom of pan.
Add blueberries and sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over top.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of fruit layer.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Top with pecans.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
After 25 minutes, take a spoon and cut down through cake to the bottom of pan in several places to permit juices to come through cake.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: In ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread smoothly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa. Pour hot water over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Great topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water enough to cover.
Remove chicken. Cook spaghetti in broth until done and drain.
Cut cheese and melt in hot spaghetti.
Cook onion in margarine on low heat until tender.
Add to spaghetti.
Add tomatoes, peas, pimento and boned, cut up chicken.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Do not bake until ready to serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths. Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar and ground cinnamon in a bowl. Coat biscuits in sugar/cinnamon mixture. Place biscuits in a greased Bundt pan. Preheat oven to 350°. Bring butter, 1 cup brown sugar, water and nuts to a boil for 2 minutes. Pour butter mixture over biscuits until all are covered. Bake for 25 minutes or until done.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add well-beaten eggs and mix until smooth.
Sift the flour once before measuring.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together and add alternately with sour milk and mashed bananas.
Beat well and add flavoring. Place in 2 greased and floured layer cake pans and bake approximately 30 minutes in 350° oven.
When cool, frost cake with 7 minute or any white vanilla frosting.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit. Keep 1/3 cup
mandarin orange juice and 2/3 cup pineapple juice.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Stir in oleo, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form this mixture into a crust in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cook meat until tender and browned; drain.
Stir in sauce; add green pepper.
Pour meat sauce over crust; top with shredded Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Brown chicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: chinese pork
directions: Slowly brown pork with salt and onions in oil.
Add the hot water and chicken bouillon; cover and cook slowly for 10 minutes. Add celery; cover and cook another 5 minutes.
Add pepper; cover and cook slowly 5 to 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, soy sauce, gravy sauce and cold water.
Add to meat; cook until thickened. Serve with rice.

title: kringla
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together the oleo, sugar and egg.
Then add the buttermilk, sour cream, vanilla and spice.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and soda and mix by hand.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll small bits of dough on floured board into strips the size of a pencil and shape into a figure 8. Bake in preheated hot oven, probably 435°, until slightly brown; don't overbake.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks and whites.
Stir in jam.
Re-sift flour with other dry ingredients.
Add flour in about three parts alternately with sour cream.
Beat batter after each addition until well blended.
Bake cake in two greased 9-inch layer pans or 9-inch tube pan in moderate 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice as desired.

title: rich cranberry shake
directions: Pour all ingredients into a blender and blend.
Pour into a glass.

title: two meat casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add Ragu sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer the sauce for 45 minutes.
Layer:
1/4 sauce, 1/4 shells, 1/4 sour cream, 1/4 Provolone cheese and 1/4 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers until all items have been used.
Top with grated Romano cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, juice, peel and vanilla, mixing at medium speed.
Blend in egg.
Pour over vanilla wafers in cupcake papers in cupcake pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pans, then chill.
Then top with strawberry preserves.

title: potato soup (caldo de papas)
directions: Saute onion until limp; add garlic and tomatoes.
Stir for a minute.
Add potatoes and stir to pick up flavor from the first 3 ingredients.
Pour in cup of beef broth and add water to fill your soup pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste when boiling.
Turn flame to simmer about 20 minutes when potatoes are soft.
Add cheese and canned milk.
Stir until cheese melts. Will feed 4.
Time for complete meal is 30 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider, cloves, allspice, cinnamon and sugar.
Boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain cloves, allspice and cinnamon.
Slice orange and add to cider bowl.

title: sheila's tortilla roll-ups
directions: Chop onions finely.
Spread large flour tortilla out.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Add 1/2 cup onions.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Slice into 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve plain or with your choice of salsa or picante.

title: delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs.
Top with chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36.

title: uno all mints
directions: Cook until soft-ball stage, 238°. Pour out on greased marble slab. When a little cool, work to a cream with wooden paddle. Cut in small pieces.

title: easy pepperoni bread
directions: Stretch French bread into large rectangle.
Place pieces of pepperoni on bread covering it, but leaving a border.
Place Provolone on top of pepperoni the same way.
Fold edges of bread to make a border, then fold lengthwise each side to center and fold once more to overlap.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken, salt, pepper, onions and sherry with enough water to cover for 1 hour.
Debone and cut chicken into chunks. Save onions and use liquid to make rice according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients including cooked onions.
Put into greased casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge dream bars
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa over low heat.
Beat eggs well.
Sift in sugar and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Pour cocoa mixture into eggs.
Blend.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brian's brownies
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and 4 squares chocolate over low heat in a heavy saucepan.
Cool.
Stir in sugar.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour, salt and 1 teaspoon of vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or just until firm.
Do not overbake.
Melt remaining 1/2 cup butter and 1 square of chocolate over low heat in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in powdered sugar, blending well.
Remove from heat.
Add egg, vanilla and lemon juice.
Stir in pecans.
Spread frosting over warm brownies.

title: ham and cheese puff
directions: Toss bread, ham and cheese in greased baking dish. Saut onion in butter until tender. Transfer onion to bowl. Add eggs, milk and mustard. Mix together. Pour over the bread mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted in the middle comes out clean. Serve immediately. Serves 12 to 15.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello, sugar, cornstarch and boiling water.
Boil until thickened.
Let cool and fold in strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill and serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: gift giving carrot cakes
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Beat eggs, sugar, mayonnaise, pineapple and reserved pineapple juice in a bowl. Gradually beat in flour mixture until well mixed.
Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Turn into greased and floured pans (two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaves).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until center is done (not gooey).
Cool and frost with white or silky lemon frosting.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Soak dried apples in water, to cover, overnight.
Drain well. Combine apples and molasses; cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, 20 minutes or until apples absorb molasses.
Set aside.

title: glass candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo to hard crack.
Remove from heat. Add oil and coloring.
Spread powdered sugar on a jelly roll pan. Pour mixture in pan.
When cool, sprinkle powdered sugar on top. Take out of pan.
Break with hammer or metal knife.

title: fudge
directions: Combine semi-sweet chocolate pieces, sweet cooking chocolate, marshmallow cream and nuts into large bowl and set aside.
Combine sugar, salt, butter or margarine and evaporated milk in a heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling stirring constantly.
Boil 6 minutes stirring often.
Pour at once over chocolate mixture in bowl; stir vigorously with wooden or nylon spoon until chocolate is melted and mixture is creamy.
Pour into buttered shallow pan.
(I use a jelly roll pan.
Can use a small cookie sheet.)
Let stand a few hours to set; overnight is good, morning until afternoon is good.
Cut into squares and store in tightly covered container.
If you plan to keep it very long, it has to be refrigerated or it will mold in time.
Good for Christmas and entertaining.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter, marshmallows and oil.
Pour over popcorn and add M&M's.
Put into pan and let cool.

title: rice chicken casserole
directions: Cook breasts until done.
Remove and add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Add cooked rice (as directed on package), then add soup.
Pour into baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inches).
Place broccoli around edge of dish.
Place chicken down center of dish.
Lay pimento in for garnish.
Cover and cook at 350° or until broccoli is done, 20 to 30 minutes.
Can add more broth if needed.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Combine spinach and all remaining ingredients
in casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco mix; blend well.
Spread on large serving plate.
Mix refried beans and taco sauce (enough to soften beans to spread).
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Layer remaining ingredients; top with a little taco or picante sauce. Serve with taco chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare apples and nuts.
Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together salt, soda, baking powder and flour.
Add gradually.
The batter will be too stiff to use electric mixer.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into 2 deep 9-inch pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
The top will be crusty.
Requires no icing.

title: luncheon chicken salad
directions: Blend Miracle Whip, sour cream, salt and lemon juice.
Fold in chicken, celery, mushrooms and bacon.
Chill well before serving on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with grapes.
Serve with ice tea and assorted crackers and cheese.

title: marshmallow candy
directions: Boil on medium heat.
Heat the ingredients until it comes to a boil.
When you take this off, add 1 1/2 cups peanut butter, 1 jar of marshmallow cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until thick and clear.
Pour over peaches that have been sliced into the baked pie crust. Refrigerate, then top with whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put into 2 pie pans; bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This makes its own crust.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine and mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add Wesson oil, eggs and carrot baby food; mix. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: *May substitute butter or margarine for paraffin wax.

title: colleen greene's no fail custard pie
directions: Beat eggs
until
frothy.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla. Beat well.
Slowly
add	scalded
milk.	Pour
into pie shell. Bake 25 minutes
at
or until it browns.
(Colleen baked her pie at 350°.) The	pie
sets some after you take it out of the oven.

title: lucky if you have any left
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, margarine, 2 tablespoons sugar and pecans.
Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: bierocks
directions: Brown ground beef; add finely chopped cabbage and onions. Season to taste.
Simmer about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: goody goody
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: german chocolate cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and blend well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in Dutch oven and pour off excess fat.
Combine soup, gravy, celery, parsley, m.s.g., green pepper and salt. Blend well.
Pour soup mixture over roast.
Simmer, covered, 2 hours or until roast is tender. Add carrots and potatoes, simmering until vegetables are heated through.
Serve with rice.

title: millie's popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn.
Place in large pan.
Combine syrup, sugar, water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Add cream of tartar.
Boil to soft crack stage (275° to 280°).
Remove from fire.
Add butter, baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and make into balls. For extra color, add gumdrops and food coloring.

title: hot chocolate mix(homemade)
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
Put 1/4 cup of mixture in a cup and add hot water.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onions thinly; steam until tender.
Drain and press out most of the water.
Turn out into a shallow casserole dish.
Using a pastry blender, chop the veggies to a lumpy, mashed consistency, blending in the butter and pepper to taste.
Bake, uncovered, about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake from 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and refrigerate.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and rinse.
Cut up all vegetables and mix together.
Before serving, add beans, crushed chips, hamburger, dressing and cheese.
Mix well and serve.

title: easy barbecued beef ribs
directions: Wipe ribs with damp paper towels.
Place ribs in a single layer in a shallow pan.
Roast ribs at 450 degrees about twenty minutes, turn once.
Mix basting sauce ingredients.
Remove ribs from oven. Brush ribs with sauce.
Return to oven.
Bake at 450 degrees for about 20 minutes longer, basting with remaining sauce.

title: microwave polish pierogi
directions: Cut the cream cheese into the flour with pastry blender.
Add butter, eggs and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Mix well and knead until smooth.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook for 12 minutes on medium heat; remove and add coconut and pecans.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tortillas and only half the cheeses.
Put 3 tablespoons of mixture in each tortilla.
Roll up and place in a greased baking dish.
Pour rest of mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine oats, all-purpose flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir to combine.
Stir in raisins and apples.

title: red raspberry squares
directions: Mix flour, margarine, salt, sugar and baking powder as for pie crust.
In a small bowl, mix yolks, milk and vanilla.
Mix all together and add to above ingredients.
Make dough and chill for 1 hour.
After chilling, take over 1/2 of the dough and put in cookie sheet (I rolled between wax paper first).
Spread raspberry pie filling or kind you desire over dough.
Lattice work over filling or a thin top crust.
Bake.
Cool until completely cool and then ice.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in salt, baking powder, cake flour and vanilla.
Roll out to 1/8-inch and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix together dates, sugar, nuts, flour and baking powder, then add milk and pinch of salt.
Pour in a deep baking pan.
Bring to a boil the brown sugar, water and butter.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips and place in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams.
Save juice.
Melt butter in 4-quart pan.
Add onion, potatoes, 1 1/2 cups water and 1/2 cup clam juice (drained from clams).
Cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add clams, 1 1/2 cups milk and cream.
Blend 1/2 cup milk and flour.
Stir into chowder.
Heat to boiling, stirring mixture while it heats.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and dash of pepper.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour.
Cook onion in oil until tender.
Brown meat on both sides in oil and onion mixture.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Prepare double crust pie recipe; roll out 1/2 of dough.
Place in 9-inch pie pan; set aside.
Peel and slice apples into 6 sections, removing all of core.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; set aside.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and cinnamon thoroughly; sprinkle over prepared apples and toss thoroughly.
Arrange apple mixture in pie pan; dot with butter.
Roll out top crust; cover apple filling.
Cut slits in top center.
Sprinkle top crust with flour-sugar mixture, then a slight sprinkle of water.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue to bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and add taco seasoning according to directions.
While beef is cooking, beat together cream cheese and onion dip on medium speed until well blended.
Spread cream cheese mixture about 1/2-inch thick on bottom of serving plate; refrigerate.
After beef is cooked and seasoned, refrigerate just until cool.
After cream cheese mixture has set up and beef is cool, spread the beef on top of the cream cheese, then top with lettuce, Cheddar cheese, tomatoes, onions and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate the cabbage, carrot, onion, pepper and cucumber.
Put in the horseradish and mix it all together.
In a separate bowl mix the salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Pour it over cole slaw and mix.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour over 4 to 6 chopped apples, 1/4 pound cheese, 2 cups chunk pineapple and nuts.
Dressing should not be real thick.

title: macaroni and chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into buttered baking dish (9 x 13).
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach.
Mix spinach, mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, water chestnuts and both soup mixes together. Set aside.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and drain potatoes.
Mix sugar, lemon and spices together.
Add eggs and milk; mix well in mixer.
Pour into pie shells.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Cook for 10 minutes the rhubarb and 2 quarts of water. Strain; add sugar, 2 cups water, lemon juice and ginger ale. Also, add pineapple juice.

title: manhattan deli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Blend cocoa, sugar, cream, syrup, butter and salt into heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over moderately high heat.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: russian fruit cake
directions: All ingredients may be "more or less".
No baking!
No flour! No sugar!

title: rhonda beans(the best barbecue beans you will ever eat!)
directions: Drain beans in a colander.
Cook and drain ground meat.
Add beans, sauce, onion and bell pepper.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: soft cut out cookies
directions: Mix the first five ingredients thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and stir in.
Roll out thick (1/4 inch).
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: plain good meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk; stir in bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sage and pepper.
Add meat and mix well.
Pat mixture into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Remove from oven and spoon off excess fat.
Combine catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard and spread over meat loaf.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal flapjacks
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add buttermilk and butter or margarine.
Stir just until mixed.
Let stand 5 minutes before pouring flapjacks on hot griddle.
Makes about 18 flapjacks.

title: chicke-n-rice
directions: Boil chicken until tender, then remove skin and set aside. Then mix soup, water, rice, salt and pepper to taste.
Spread rice mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Lay chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Cover tightly with lid or foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix spinach, cream cheese, brick cheese, eggs and margarine. Sprinkle garlic, onion flakes and chives.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grated sweet potato pie
directions: Mix and place in your favorite uncooked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Place each chicken breast half on a sheet of wax paper. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Place 1 piece of ham and cheese in center of each chicken piece. Roll up lengthwise and secure with toothpicks.

title: shrewsbury cake(this sugar crusted cake needs no frosting!)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating for five minutes after each addition.
Add flour and baking powder, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan for 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven. Test for doneness with a toothpick and cool right side up.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven. Cover with marshmallows.
Brown lightly.

title: tammy's lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add spaghetti sauce.
In boiling water cook lasagne
noodles; mix cheeses together.
Layer
noodles,
meat and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat second
layer.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: plum muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and baking powder.
Cut in oleo. Mix yogurt, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together and fold in plums. Heat oven to 400°.
Pour batter into greased muffin pans.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine cinnamon and sugar and set aside.
Heat milk and butter until butter melts.
In large bowl combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt, eggs and milk and butter mix.
Mix with doughmaker at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and knead for 3 more minutes.
If dough is sticky, add remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn over to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double.
Roll out with rolling pin until 1/4 inch thick and butter it.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Roll up and slice in 1 inch or 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: baked spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground sirloin beef, then drain and set aside.
Cook pasta according to directions.
After draining, put pasta back in same pot.
Add ground beef and large jar of spaghetti sauce; mix together.
Put half of mixture into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish; place Parmesan cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese for middle layer.
Pour remaining mix on top of this.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Put in preheated oven and bake for 35 minutes.
Warm small jar of spaghetti sauce for topping.
Perfect with rolls and salad.
Enjoy!

title: million dollar dessert
directions: First Layer:
Combine flour and butter until crumbly.
Press into a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: cheese chili pepper roll-up(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Dry chilies on paper towels to remove all oil.
Roll Velveeta into 9 to 10-inch circle.
Place between sheets of waxed paper. Stir cream cheese until smooth and spread over Velveeta.
Finely dice green chilies and spread on cream cheese.
Roll and cover with Saran Wrap.
Wrap with foil if freezing.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm butter thins.
Keeps up to 6 weeks in freezer.

title: calvin's stirred eggs
directions: Cook bacon in a cast-iron skillet until about 1/2 done.
Break eggs into bacon grease.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir all together until eggs and bacon are done to your taste.
Best if cooked over a campfire but may be cooked inside on the stove.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over high heat, heat unpeeled potatoes and enough water to cover.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until potatoes are fork-tender.
Drain. Cool potatoes slightly.
Peel and dice potatoes.

title: easy cheese bars
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pat out one package crescent rolls.
Pinch together perforations.
On top of that, put mixture of 2 (8 ounce) packages cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 eggs, creamed together until smooth.
Then put in another package of crescent rolls on top of cream cheese mixture for top crust.
Pinch together again.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter on top of crust.
Then sprinkle mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasoning.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 to 20 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Serve over rice with crackers or hot French bread.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar until lemon colored.
Add eggs one at a time while beating.
Add alternately the milk and vanilla wafers.
Add coconut and nuts. Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Can serve plain with whipped cream or can frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, eggs and onion.
Mix with broccoli and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix margarine and stuffing mix together and put on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy cucumber pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice 1/2 inch thick.
Boil sugar and vinegar together for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to hot vinegar and pour over pickles.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, vanilla, margarine and peanut butter in pan; bring to a boil.
Boil for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.

title: chicken in a flash
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Add chicken before cooking the rice; that's it.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken, pick off the bone and shred.
Finely chop onion and saute in butter.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and soup.
Heat mixture until smooth.
In large casserole dish, layer tortillas, soup mixture and chicken, then cheese, until dish is full.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 350°.
Remove immediately from pan.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix wet ingredients. Mix and add dry ingredients. Cook on griddle or skillet at about 365° until bubbles form on top. Turn and brown on other side.

title: salsa
directions: Combine the first 11 ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Chop all the spices and add to the sauce. Remove from heat, chill and serve.

title: tom and jerry batter
directions: Beat yolks until thick. Add cornstarch. Beat whites until stiff.
Add powdered sugar.
Now mix all together with flavoring and enjoy.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
Add sour cream to jello and beat well.
Strain berries and use juice to make 2 1/2 cups of liquid.
Add berries and liquid altogether to jello mixture.
Pour into mold that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello with boiling water and cold pineapple juice. Allow to cool and partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into mold.
Place in refrigerator.
Prepare a day or so ahead of serving.

title: terrific baked beans
directions: Drain liquid off beans, except pork and beans.
Cool bacon and onion.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large casserole. If desired, put strips of bacon over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered; uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 250° for 2 hours.
(Okay to use 2 cups chopped pecans if desired.)
Preheat oven.

title: bean soup
directions: Place beans and ham in a pot.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
When water has come to a boil, turn heat down to a simmer, cover pot.
You will cook the beans and ham about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
About 1 hour before soup is finished put celery, carrots and onion in the pot.
About 30 minutes before the soup is finished, put the potatoes in the pot.
Add horseradish to soup by taste.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Soak tortillas in chicken broth until wilted; reserve broth. Place tortillas in greased 2-quart baking dish, covering sides and bottom.
Combine chicken, onion, chili powder and garlic salt. Place mixture on tortillas.
Mix remaining chicken broth with milk, flour and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Add chiles and tomatoes and top with grated cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruity cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mash bananas; add dates and oil.	Mix well with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and let stand a few minutes for oats to absorb moisture.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes or until browned. Cool before removing from pan.

title: ms. toole's spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat. Add Ragu sauce, tomatoes, potatoes, carrots and cayenne pepper. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over noodles. Enjoy!

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cut up dates and put in big skillet. Add oleo and sugar.
Cook until dissolved, stirring constantly.
Beat egg and add to mixture. Cook until done (4 to 5 minutes). Add vanilla.
Pour over Rice Krispies and pecans; stir until mixed.
Cool until you can handle. Grease hands with oleo and lightly press into balls. Roll in coconut.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat egg whites. Mix sugar and flour thoroughly.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add beaten egg yolks and remaining milk.
Fold in melted butter.
Slowly pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 425° until knife is inserted and comes out clean.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop green onions and water chestnuts really fine.
Squeeze all the water out of the spinach and mix all together.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: nachos
directions: Mix together and heat until completely melted. Serve with nacho chips.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Put 1/4 of soup in meat mixture.
Make into meatballs.
Brown and drain grease off.
Pour the rest of soup plus water over top and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: coconut surprise
directions: Mix together flour and melted margarine.
Spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Saute onions, pepper and celery until soft.
Add hamburg and simmer until cooked through.
Add tomato soup and water.
Simmer until it thickens.
Pour in pie shell.
Cover with rest of pie dough.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: undercover brown beans
directions: Brown meat; season to taste and drain.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix up corn bread and spread evenly over entire mixture.
Bake at 400° until corn bread is browned.
Great for left over beans.
Can use ground turkey.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour.
In 6-quart Dutch oven, heat oil.
Brown meat in oil.
Remove meat from pan as it browns.
Leave meat drippings in pan and add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in 3 or 4 tablespoons of flour and 1 cup of water.
Cook until thickened. Add tomato paste, seasoning mix, salt and rest of water (add water gradually).
Stir until smooth.
Add meat and heat to boiling; stir constantly.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add carrots and cook 1/2 hour. Add potatoes and cook until carrots and potatoes are done.
Add peas and heat 5 minutes more.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: The day before, combine cheese, spinach, carrot, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate.
Remove stems from washed tomatoes, cut in half and scoop out pulp.
Let drain upside down on paper towels.
Cover and refrigerate.
Next day, fill tomatoes with cheese mixture and chill until served.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Crumble.
Mix cream cheese with sausage.
Spread rolls out flat on long pan sprayed with Pam. Spread sausage mixture over roll.
Roll up and bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and add jello until dissolved.
Set off burner to cool.
Add buttermilk to Cool Whip.
Add pineapple mixture. Keeps well.
Serves 12.

title: two step sour cream pound cake
directions: You will need a heavy-duty stand mixer with a 4 qt. bowl and paddle attachment.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease bundt pan with 2 Tbsp.
Crisco.
In mixing bowl, place ingredients in the following order:
flour, salt, sugar, crisco, sour cream mixed with soda, eggs, vanilla and lemon extracts.
Beat at low speed for 1 minute, scraping sides down.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into bundt pan and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Resist temptation to peek.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add hot water in punch bowl.
Then add other ingredients.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour until smooth. Bring milk to boil. Add dry mixture and cook until thickens. Add butter and vanilla. Serve on hot biscuits.

title: mexican rice
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add rice; set aside.
Put 3 tablespoons butter in frying pan.
Add the chopped onion and chopped mushrooms.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add the soy sauce, several dashes of hot sauce, dash of garlic salt and black pepper. Pour rice into frypan.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add the sour cream (optional).

title: grandma koening's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Remove and peel skin.
Cut potatoes into chunks.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Dice onion, pickles, celery and eggs.
Place in bowl with potatoes.
Mix dressing and mustard together.
Add to potato mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: rum or bourbon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together using about one rounded teaspoonful of the mixture; form small balls.
Roll in extra powdered sugar or chopped nuts.
Store in tightly covered container.
Layer with wax paper, making sure they are not crowded.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix together sour cream and peaches.
Fold in dry ingredients alternately with sour cream and peaches.
Stir in vanilla and almond extracts.

title: fudgy chocolate cookie bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into flour and brown chicken so you have a little crust.
Place chicken in casserole dish; pour Ragu sauce over your chicken.
Cook about 45 minutes. Place cheese over the top and place back in oven about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: angel custard dessert
directions: Combine egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind; cook until thickened and remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in water.
Beat egg whites and remaining 3/4 cup sugar until stiff and fold into gelatin.
Tear cake into small pieces and fold custard into cake.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: ham and raisins
directions: Brown a thick slice of ham in hot skillet.
Mix ingredients and boil for a few minutes.
Put ham in a baking dish and pour mixture over it.
Cover and bake 45 minutes in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients lightly; shape and place in an uncovered pan.

title: larry's famous silver dollar pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a mixing bowl with a large mixing spoon. Finish the mixing by using a fork, making sure all the Bisquick is mixed and not in clumps. You may want to add a little more milk if it's too thick, but not much. Get a skillet and spray some nonstick into it, then wipe out lightly with a paper towel. Set the heat to medium and using a serving spoon, dip out the batter into the skillet. Flip the pancakes when brown on the bottom side and cook the other side.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix loose sausage meat, cheese and Bisquick together.
Shape into small balls, about 1 1/2-inches in size.
Bake on cookie tray at 350° for 30 minutes if frozen or for 20 minutes if thawed. Delicious.
Makes 100 cocktail balls.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in crust.
Refrigerate.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn.
Reserve liquid.
Add milk to liquid to measure 1 cup. Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk mixture and corn.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and chill.
Form in ball and roll in parsley and chopped walnuts.

title: chili moi
directions: Chop onion.
Brown meat in hot pan.
Add remaining ingredients; cook until meat is tender.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and broccoli in butter for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.
Place rice in 8-inch square dish.
Pour cheese mix over rice.
DO NOT STIR! Bake uncovered at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Mix next 4 ingredients in separate bowl.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine.
When golden brown, add flour and stir until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer all together for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Will be deeper brown than regular cornbread.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, cream cheese,
mayonnaise and pecans.
Pour in 1 cup water.
Mix again.
Add pineapple and milk.
Stir until thickened.
Chill 24 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add the eggs (well beaten), vanilla, the flour (sifted with the salt and soda), then the peanut butter.
Mix well and knead.
Roll into balls about 3/4 inch across.
Place 1 inch apart on greased pans.
Press with fork lengthwise, then crosswise.
Bake at 400° from 5 to 10 minutes.

title: grilled short ribs
directions: Arrange short ribs in shallow baking pan.
Cover with foil. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Stir together mustard, tomato juice and molasses.
Brush over baked short ribs.
Grill over hot coals for 20 to 30 minutes until tender, turning frequently and brushing with mustard mixture.
Makes four to six servings.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Mix ingredients one at a time.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cauliflower-potato soup
directions: Combine broth, cauliflower, leeks (or onion) and potato in 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Place vegetables, 2 cups at a time, in bowl of food processor or blender; puree.
Return to saucepan.
Add half and half, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Heat through; do not boil.
Dot with butter and sprinkle of nutmeg.
Yields 6 servings.

title: aunt helen's hominy casserole
directions: Place onion and margarine in saucepan.
Saute until onion is clear.
Add cheese and soup.
Stir until smooth.
Add hominy. Pour into casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: steak with roquefort butter
directions: Marinate flank steak in French dressing for several hours. Remove flank steak from marinade and broil on both sides. Transfer to platter and slice diagonally into 1/4-inch strips. Spoon Roquefort butter over meat.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well dampened.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.

title: green bean soup
directions: Cook ham bone in water until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Remove meat from bone.
Put meat back in soup base.
Add green beans, potatoes, onions, parsley, savory, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil or until vegetables are tender.
Skim off excess fat. Just before serving, stir in light cream.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Mix everything together. Chill until ready to serve.

title: hawaiian christmas pie(prepared in layers)
directions: Layer 1:
Mix margarine, sugar and graham crackers and spread in oblong dish.

title: cheese and bacon puffs
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Combine with mayo, cheese, onions, sherry and seasonings to taste.
Mix well. Chill 3 hours or up to 3 days.
Spread on Melba rounds.
Broil until bubbly.
Watch.
Yields about 50.

title: banana julies
directions: Combine all in blender and blend well.

title: beans and noodles
directions: Cook beef, drain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until hot.
Serve.

title: pork piccata(this dish tastes delicious served with rice)
directions: Cube tomatoes and place in medium bowl.
Saute garlic and onion in 1 pound of oil until golden brown and add to tomatoes. Add remaining ingredients into bowl with tomatoes, oil, basil, parsley, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Cook 1 pound of pasta; drain and add tomato mix on top of pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: mrs. bailey's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
In large bowl, sift together 4 cups flour and baking soda.
Cut in lard until it looks like coarse crumbs.
Mix together the remaining 1 cup flour with buttermilk and yeast mixture to the flour mixture.
Mix well. Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead.
Place in greased bowl, covered, in refrigerator.
Biscuits are ready to bake at any time.
When you are ready to bake, roll out and cut as many as needed.
Bake in a 425° oven for about 15 minutes.
Yields about 3 dozen biscuits.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Dissolve soda in milk.
Mix ingredients, put in cake pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly brown around edges.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix and spread in greased 6x10 inch pan.
Bake until brown at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: jello slice
directions: Arrange whole vanilla or graham wafers in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top with whipped topping.
Arrange whole wafers on top.
Put thickened Jell-O pudding on top.
Add rest of whipped topping. Sprinkle crushed wafers over top.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Very light and tasty after a big meal.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in 2 tablespoons butter and remove from pan.
Remove fat and bone from steak.
Cut into strips 2 1/2 inches long and 3/4-inch wide.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in pan. Toss meat in flour, coating thoroughly.
Brown meat in butter and add salt and bouillon water mixture.
Simmer, stirring occasionally until meat is tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
Add mushrooms, onions and sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in 1-quart loaf pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry, banana nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water; add pineapple (juice and all), strawberries, bananas and pecans.
Pour 1/2 mixture in oblong dish; chill in freezer until firm.
Then spread 1 container sour cream over mixture and add remaining 1/2 of mixture and chill.

title: tomato soup cake (spice cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and spices.
Combine baking powder and flour.
Combine soda and soup (this will swell).
Add flour mixture and soup mixture alternately with butter mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. (For variety, add raisins and nuts.)

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken in a large greased casserole dish.
Mix soups, broth and canned vegetables and pour evenly over chicken.

title: pace con queso dip
directions: Combine cubed cheese, milk and picante sauce in a saucepan over low heat.
Heat until sauce is smooth.
Serve with chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: butter pecan squares
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour and 1/3 cup sugar in a medium bowl; cut in 1/2 cup butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press mixture evenly into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Combine next 7 ingredients and beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour filling over prepared crust. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm.
Let cool on rack; cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: deviled dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve as a dip or eat with crackers.

title: nancy's teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate steak or chicken for 4 to 12 hours in refrigerator. Broil or grill.

title: pralines
directions: Butter sides of a 3-quart pan.
Combine sugar, cream and baking soda.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add 2 cups of pecans or walnuts.
Beat until it begins to thicken. Using 2 tablespoons, make small mounds on wax paper.
Remove when cool.

title: cherry date bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, eggs, butter.
Add dates and soda to boiling water, then mix with butter and sugar.
Add the flour, baking powder, nuts and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill 1 hour.
Garnish with cherries or strawberries.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Wash and cut cabbage into strips; set aside.
Fry bacon in heavy pot.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
After about 10 minutes, stir to mix in seasonings and coat cabbage with bacon fat.
Cook, stirring occasionally, to desired crispness.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be very thick. When adding flour, add 1 cup at a time.
Bake in angel food cake pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: travel mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
You can add different of your favorite candies and nuts if you wish, too.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly with electric mixer.
Add egg yolks, flour, Grape-Nuts, milk and lemon juice and rind.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks.
Fold (beat well) egg whites into mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish, placed in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 375° on bottom rack for 50 to 60 minutes.
When done, pudding will have a crust on top and jelly on bottom.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 4 to 6. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs. Layer in casserole dish, hamburger, pizza sauce, cheese and Bisquick mixture.
Cook in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lima con carne
directions: Wash soybeans and then remove any foreign particles. Cover soybeans with cold water.
Refrigerate or freeze overnight. Freezing will lessen the amount of cooking time needed.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cold water, crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill overnight.
Use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Next morning, combine pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg.
Cook until thick.
Cool and pour over Jell-O.
Beat until smooth Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Spread over Jell-O.
Top with grated cheese.

title: sunday night biscuits
directions: Mix up and drop into muffin tin with paper liners. Cook at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Bring half and half to boil in a heavy saucepan.
Add potatoes, butter, salt and pepper.
Simmer slowly until it thickens.
Pour into a baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and a little melted butter.
Place under broiler to brown.
Serves 4 to 6.
May be made a day ahead or may be frozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Put in lightly greased casserole dish.
Set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, mushroom soup, eggs, cheese and margarine.
Mix well and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle crushed cracker crumbs on top and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: crisp corn sticks
directions: Mix sifted cornmeal, salt and baking soda.
Add oil and stir, then add buttermilk and syrup.
Stir well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder soda and cinnamon.
Mix together zucchini, vanilla, oil, eggs and sugar.
Mix well and pour into flour mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Turn into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup water and set aside.
Stir-fry beef in 1 tablespoon hot oil; remove.
Add 1 more tablespoon oil; saute pepper and onion with garlic.
Add consomme and cornstarch mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir constantly. Add beef and heat.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp appetizer spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream and mayo; mix well.
Spread mixture on a round 12 in. serving platter.
Sprinkle with shrimp.
Top with seafood sauce.
Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese, green pepper, tomato, and onions.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Sprinkle in the chopped pecans.
Place frozen rolls on top of pecans.
Mix brown sugar and pudding mix and sprinkle over rolls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over pudding mix.
Pour melted butter over all.
Place in cold oven overnight, uncovered.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar, then add ingredients, except miniature marshmallows, in order given.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.
Take out of oven. Pour the miniature marshmallows on top; put back into oven until melted.
Cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna until tender.
Brown the sausage and hamburger. Then drain off excess grease.
Next, lay pasta in pan.
Apply butter over noodles, a layer of sauce, cottage cheese, hamburger, sausage, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella and pepperoni.
Repeat until contents are used.
Top with layer of noodles.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Contents should be moist and hot.

title: lemon snowballs
directions: Mix margarine, flour and sugar.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 325° for 18 minutes while cooking.
Beat together eggs, 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, baking powder and lemon juice. Pour over flour mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes until set.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over top.
Cool.

title: apple crisp a la francoise
directions: Crisp:
Mix oats, flour, cinnamon and butter.
Cut into mixture, using 2 knives until pea size.

title: paul's monkey bread
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Cut biscuits into quarters. Toss in bowl with sugar, cinnamon and butter mix.
Stir into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Combine in double boiler the soup, milk and Velveeta cheese. When melted and creamy, add green chilies.
In frying pan, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in grated cheese.
Warm tortillas in foil in oven.
Place small amount of meat mixture in center of each tortilla.
Roll and place side by side in baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over rolled tortillas.
Cover; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Also good when topped with sour cream or when chicken is substituted for beef.

title: chocolate skillet pie
directions: Mix together 1 cup of sugar, flour and cocoa.
Slightly beat egg yolks; add milk.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet; stir in sugar, flour, cocoa mixture and enough milk to be able to mix well. Remove from heat; stir in remaining milk.
Stir again over heat until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff; beat in 6 tablespoons sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Put on top of pie.
Bake at 325° to brown. Yields 6 servings.

title: fruity dessert
directions: Spread can of pineapple in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with can of pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top; top with nuts.
Cut sticks of margarine into chunks and put on top of nuts.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carol's enchilada goo!
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tortillas and hamburger meat.
Put on low heat; stir constantly.
After melted, add hamburger meat and set aside.
Put tortillas on bottom of a very large rectangular pan.
Put a layer of hamburger mixture, then tortillas, then hamburger
mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes at least 20 servings.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone and chop up or you can cook 4 to 5 chicken breasts.
To chicken add can of soup and sour cream. Put in casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs, melted oleo and poppy seed.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put chicken in shallow pan.
Pour dressing over chicken (just to cover it).
Cover with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and add salad oil, cinnamon, sugar and vanilla.
Mix together flour, soda and salt and add to egg mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in apples and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 10 x 18-inch ungreased pan.

title: mint pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients just before serving.

title: kashi breakfast
directions: Put 2 cups water or fruit juice in saucepan.
Add apple pieces, raisins and kashi.
Simmer for 30 minutes (until liquid is absorbed).
Serve warm with yogurt.
Keep in refrigerator.
Warm up in microwave.

title: refrigerator fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Turn heat low. Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat, immediately add chocolate bits, Karo, butter and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate melts and fudge is smooth and creamy.
Stir in nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and chill in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.
Keep in refrigerator until used.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken. Cook spaghetti.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in butter 5 minutes.
Mix everything except the spaghetti and 1/4 of the cheese. Add spaghetti and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together; save part of the cheese to spread on top. Cover and bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Butter cold buns.
Add filling.
Wrap in foil and heat in oven for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: savory beef stew
directions: Brown beef cubes on all sides in oil.
