Bring onion, tomatoes, beef broth, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper, bay leaf and tapioca to a boil; place beef cubes in 3-quart casserole.
Pour above mixture over beef.
Cover; bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes and celery; continue baking 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Make Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add 7-Up.
Add crushed pineapple.
Pour into pan and add marshmallows before it thickens.

title: aunt liz's whipping cream biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
(Dough will be stiff.) Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll dough to 3/8-inch thickness; cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together until well blended.
Add chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased or Pammed Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: crunchy vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
Pour salad dressing over and toss to coat evenly.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: corned beef pinwheels
directions: Combine in a 9 x 9-inch pan the gravy mix and water. Bring to a boil in a 375° oven.

title: dot's lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and rinse with cold water.
Cook hamburger; drain and add to spaghetti sauce.
Cover bottom of pans lightly with meat sauce.
Put 2 layers of noodles on that.
Spread half of Ricotta cheese on top of noodles and half of Mozzarella cheese.
Put half of meat sauce on top.
Add another 2 layers of noodles and rest of Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Place sliced or shredded Provolone cheese on top of that and add rest of meat sauce. Sprinkle with grated Romano cheese and bake at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 1 large and 1 small dish.
Delicious.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix well.
Put into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and cream cheese.
Beat all together and pur on graham cracker crust.
Let set overnight.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet.

title: creole bread pudding
directions: Combine bread cubes in milk; set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and margarine.
Pour over bread and milk.
Add raisins and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Place dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 300° about 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: almond punch(servings for 60)
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Mix all ingredients except 7-Ups.
Just before serving, add 7-Ups.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Heat sugar, salad oil, vinegar and salt until sugar dissolves. Cool.
Drain peas and beans.
Slice green pepper, onion, water chestnuts, radishes and cauliflower.
Pour dressing over vegetables and refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours.

title: purple ribbon chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, salt
and
soda
together;
set
aside.
Add boiling water to
chocolate
and
stir until chocolate is dissolved; set aside.
Cream shortening; add sugars gradually and cream together.
Add
eggs	and
beat well, then add chocolate mixture and blend.	Add
flour alternately with milk;
beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.	Bake in layer pans in 350° oven for 30 minutes until done.
Cover with favorite frosting.

title: layered salad
directions: Wash and tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Put in
9 x 13-inch container.
Layer in order the next 5 ingredients. Sprinkle grated cheese to cover.
Spread salad dressing over cheese to cover and seal well.
This is better if made a day ahead.
Before serving, stir well.

title: date-nut pinwheels
directions: Cook dates, sugar, water.
Add nuts when cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, 1 cup of cheese, sour cream, soup and salt and pepper in a large pot on the stove.

title: corn souffle(makes 8 servings)
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Mix in eggs, margarine, milk and corn.
Pour into well-greased 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until top is golden, crusty brown and center is firm.
Cool slightly and cut into squares in oblong pan.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain egg noodles.
Add butter and milk.
Stir.
Add mushroom soup, tuna and minced onion.
Mix and cook on low heat 15 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix dates into flour; mix orange slices, pecans and coconut into flour.
Cream oleo and sugar; add one egg at a time.
Add buttermilk into which the soda has been added.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Pour into oiled tube pan.
Bake at 250° to 275° for about 3 hours.
Glaze with 2 cups confectioners sugar mixed with 1 cup orange juice.

title: joan's easy potato surprise
directions: Layer sliced potatoes in a greased 9 x 12-inch or other appropriate baking dish (preferably not metal).
Place enough potatoes in dish to fill to top.
Sprinkle instant onion soup mix over top of potatoes.
Drizzle butter over top and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: mom's three bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon separately.
Cook hamburger with onion.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for a few hours.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: salted nut rolls
directions: Melt and stir peanut butter chips and butter in microwave or over low heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk and miniature marshmallows.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour 8 ounces of the dry roasted peanuts in bottom of pan.
Pat mixture over nuts.
Top with 8 ounces of dry roasted peanuts.

title: crunchy celery casserole
directions: Microwave celery in even layer in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover. Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes. Stir midway. Drain. Add soup, milk and pecans and stir. Sprinkle crushed crackers on top. Drizzle with margarine. May make ahead. Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add the vanilla, flour and milk; mix well.
Start in cold oven; bake at 325° for 1 hour, then at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not open oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes one 10-inch tube cake.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Melt butter in microwave oven for 30 seconds.
Add onion and heat, uncovered, in microwave oven for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook spinach; drain well.
Combine onion, spinach, salt, pepper, nutmeg and cream cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Heat, covered, in microwave oven for 5 to 6 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: tom thumb bars
directions: Combine shortening and salt.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar and cream.
Stir in flour.
Spread evenly in greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs, add brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Spread on baked mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into squares.

title: creme doodle
directions: Stir all ingredients, except coconut together and roll into balls. Roll in coconut. Chill or freeze.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour in churn.

title: peach pie (lazy man's pie)
directions: Put margarine in pan and melt. Mix sugar, flour and milk. Pour mixture over melted margarine. Add fruit. Bake at 250° until brown.

title: baked haddock
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.
On wax paper, combine crumbs, herbs, salt and pepper.
In shallow plate, beat egg with 1 teaspoon of water.
Dip fillets in egg, then in crumbs, using all of each.
Place fillets in prepared pan.
Pour melted margarine evenly over fillets.
Bake for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: church chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
When cool, debone and chop into small pieces. Place chicken in bottom of 2 quart oblong casserole dish.
Mix together 2 cans cream of chicken soup, poppy seed and sour cream. Pour mixture over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers over mixture and drizzle margarine over cracker crumbs.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking for additional 10 minutes or until casserole is bubbling. Be sure cracker crumbs are browned.
Serves 6 or more.

title: marbled cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings. Combine milk, egg yolk and melted shortening.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients; stir just until combined.
Beat egg white until stiff; fold into batter.
Heat shortening in skillet or pan to make 1 to 2 inches deep.
Dip onion rings in batter.
Fry in hot shortening about 3 minutes, turning once.
Drain on paper toweling.

title: pierogi
directions: Mix baking powder, salt and 1 cup flour.
Lightly beat egg and egg yolk.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add flour, a little at a time using the mixed flour first.
Add enough so dough can be rolled out.
Be sure it is soft and not too stiff.
Cut with large round cookie cutter.
Add filling of your choice and pinch together at seams.
Drop in boiling water.
If freezing, remove and drain as soon as the pierogi rises to the top.
If serving, cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Top with melted butter, sour cream and/or chopped onions and serve.

title: curried beans
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; blend well.
Chill.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Let egg whites stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.

title: miniature cheesecakes(serves 24)
directions: You will need 24 cupcake liners.

title: homemade shake 'n bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
This amount of mix equals 20 store-bought bags of chicken coating mix.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Combine ingredients with mixer and pour onto crust.
Chill until set.
Cover with Cool Whip and decorate with shaved chocolate, chopped nuts, sprinkles, cherries or whatever you'd like.

title: watergate salad
directions: In medium size bowl empty can of pineapple.
Add pudding, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: no knead cream cheese rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Add milk and beaten eggs, then add yeast mixture. (Make sure butter isn't hot or it'll kill the yeast.)
Add extra sugar and salt.
Stir in flour; do not get too thick or it'll make heavy dough.
Cover tightly and let stand in fridge for 6 hours, overnight or up to 2 days.
Roll dough on floured surface 1/2 inch thick.
Spread with 1/2 cup extra melted butter.

title: t's fried steak
directions: Rub steak with salt and pepper.
Pound as much flour in steak as possible.
Brown slowly on both sides in hot cooking oil.
Add water.
Cover and steam.
Simmer a few minutes until tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken my way
directions: Spray baking pan with no stick cooking oil.
Place chicken in pan.

title: gracie's stew
directions: In casserole dish, place meat on bottom.
Cover with vegetables and potatoes.
Mix all soups together.
Pour soups over meat and vegetables. Place casserole in preheated 325° oven for 3 hours.
No peeking!

title: raspberry cream
directions: Pour boiling water over jello in bowl, stirring until jello is dissolved.
Stir in ice cream and frozen fruit, breaking up berries with fork.
Chill until set, about 20 minutes.
Spoon into dessert bowls.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: zesty pumpkin soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onions and garlic until soft.
Add curry powder, salt, coriander and red pepper; cook 1 minute.
Add broth.
Boil gently, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in pumpkin and half and half; cook 5 minutes.
Pour into blender container.
Cover.
Blend until creamy.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening together.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nutmeats.
Fold in egg whites.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Make well in center of dry ingredients. Add salad oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix until smooth. Pour into 2 or 3 greased and floured 1 pound loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together until well blended.
Use for marinating with London broil, chicken or spareribs.
It's delicious!

title: hurry up veal
directions: Dip cutlet in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.
Brown in oil in skillet. Add rest of ingredients and cover.
Cook on low heat until veal is tender.

title: cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool chicken. Remove skin and debone chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Make a white sauce in large skillet over medium heat, using the butter, flour and 1 cup milk.
Add milk slowly, stirring until smooth and all milk is added.
To white sauce add the mushroom soup and 3/4 can milk.
Add cut up chicken to sauce mixture.
Serve hot over white rice or in patty shells.

title: sausage strata
directions: Toast bread lightly and fit into a greased pan, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch.
Brown sausage, drain off fat.
Stir in mustard.
Spoon sausage evenly over bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine egg, milk, Worcestershire, 1/2 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper and nutmeg.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna and mushroom sauce
directions: Heat the oil with garlic and shallots.
Add the mushrooms, sauteing for about 5 minutes or until slightly brown.
Reduce heat, add milk and simmer until it becomes creamy.
Stir in cheese, then fold in tuna and spices.
Simmer at low heat, season and pour over pasta.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla and baking powder.
Mix.
Add remaining ingredients gradually, beating well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: connie's mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8-inch round cake pans.
In mixer bowl, combine mix, oil and eggs, beat thoroughly.
Stir in oranges and their juice.
Divide batter among the prepared pans.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 - 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn out and cool on racks.

title: polynesian pork
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Lightly grease heavy skillet with fat from one chop.
Brown chops on both sides; drain off excess fat.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Drain pineapple; combine with onion, celery leaves, garlic, prunes, soy sauce and marjoram; simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add celery. Cook for 10 minutes longer or until celery is tender and pork is well done.
Add small amount of water if needed.
Prepare rice according to package.
Add ginger, stirring to blend.
Serve pork mixture over rice.

title: apricot orange-nut loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk, orange juice and rind.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in nuts and apricots.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake until toothpick stuck into center comes out clean. (Crack in top is characteristic.) Bake at 350° for about 70 minutes.

title: stir-fried steak
directions: Brown sirloin in butter.
Put meat in a large bowl.
Cut the meat into bite sizes.
In a skillet, use 2 tablespoons oil; add 2 beef bouillon cubes to the oil.
After the bouillon cubes have melted, add flour to thicken oil.
(Use your own judgement on the amount of flour for gravy.)
Put around 2 cups of water in the flour mixture.
When the gravy thickens, pour over the moist meat. Serve.
Best way to serve is with mashed potatoes with the meat.

title: five minute pie
directions: Combine pineapple with dry ingredients of pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill 1 hour.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Slice jelly rolls into 3/4-inch slices.
Use to line sides and bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Spread slightly softened heavenly hash ice cream over cake.
Spread vanilla over the heavenly hash.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cover with foil and freeze until firm.
Remove rim from pan.
Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Stir in Tabasco, onion powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut the bread slices into any shapes you wish; such as triangles, strips, rounds or squares.
Spread cheese mixture on top and sides of bread.
Sprinkle with dill weed. Arrange on baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.
They also freeze very well before baking.

title: double chocolate peppermint candy
directions: Crush mints into small pieces.
Melt chocolate separately in microwave.
Put half of mints in white chocolate and half in semi sweet chocolate. Pour onto wax paper making a marble effect.
When set, break into bite size pieces.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Combine water, oleo and flour and bring to boil.
Stir until forms a ball.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs, one at a time. Spread in a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine 1 egg, oil and all but 1 cup cake mix.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Saute meat until brown.
Saute onion; drain.
Beat eggs.
Add corn, bread mix and milk; mix well.
Preheat cast-iron skillet in oven at 350°.
Remove; grease pan.
Place 1/2 cornbread mixture into pan.
Add hamburger, onion, peppers and cheese.
Top with remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; place on wet towel for 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine poppy seed and water and let set while mixing other ingredients.
Add the water mixture to cake mixture and beat for 5 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bean-mushroom medley
directions: Heat
1-inch water to boiling in 2-quart saucepan.
Add beans and
carrots.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring
occasionally
until almost tender, about 12 minutes. Drain.
Cook
and stir onion and mushrooms in butter in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until almost tender, about 5 minutes. Reduce heat.
Cover
and
cook 3 minutes.
Stir in beans, carrots, salt, garlic
salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Set aside.
Mix the first 7 ingredients together in the order given.
Add flour mixture and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve cold.

title: daretown presbyterian church oyster pie
directions: Hard-boil 3 eggs.
Slice and lay in bottom of 9-inch pie crust. Chop up boiled potatoes.
Put dots of butter on potatoes.
Pour in oysters to fill pie.
Cover with top crust.
Prick top of pie crust before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 375° in 9-inch pie plate.
Make a thin White Sauce using 2 tablespoons oyster juice mixed in milk. Bottled clam juice can be used if oysters don't have enough juice. Pour hot White Sauce over hot pie to serve.

title: amy's mexicana casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Stir together chicken, 1 c. Cheddar, onion and sour cream.
Pour salsa into pie plate.
Coat tortilla with salsa in pie plate and place in deep round baking dish. Spread 1/2 c. chicken mixture onto tortilla.
Repeat with tortillas and chicken, topping with a tortilla.
Cover with remaining salsa and 1/2 c. Cheddar.
Cover and bake 35-40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Spoon cooked meat into 8 or 9-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine milk, eggs and Bisquick in separate bowl and beat until smooth.
Pour over top of casserole evenly.
Bake at 400° until browned, about 35 minutes.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Blend butter and carrots.
Add sugar and flour.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat in one-inch squares.
Brown meat in one tablespoon of hot shortening.
Remove from skillet; add gravy mix and two cups of water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in next 6 ingredients, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Add meat. Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Mix in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan the pudding, sugar, milk and butter. Cook and stir to a full, all over boil.
Lower heat and keep stirring while mixture boils slowly 3 minutes.
Take off heat. Stir in all at once the peanuts.
Beat until candy starts to thicken. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper to form 24 clusters.

title: corn flake chewies
directions: Combine sugar and Karo in 2-quart saucepan; bring to a bubbling boil, then add peanut butter and remove from heat.
Add corn flakes and mix well.
Drop on buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Stir together Bisquick, cheese and pepper.
Stir in eggs until moist.
Fold in zucchini.
Heat oil.
Fry 2 tablespoons mixture for each round 2 to 3 minutes per side.
Makes 12.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Add baking powder. Mix together.
Add coconut, pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Mix good, then add graham cracker crumbs and milk.
Mix until all ingredients are moist.
Pour into a tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: praline cookies
directions: Bring oleo, sugar and milk to a rolling boil, stirring constantly or it will burn.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallows and salt, stirring until marshmallows are melted.
Add crumbs, pecans and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
In bowl with electric mixer, beat on medium speed the margarine and sugar. Add egg and beat 3 minutes, scraping often. Add to flour mixture alternately with milk and vanilla, beating well.
Pour into pans. Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Spring test for doneness. Remove to rack. Cool completely.

title: peach praline shortcake
directions: Measure flour, baking powder, salt and soda into bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup brown sugar and the shortening thoroughly until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in pecans.
Combine egg and milk; stir into flour mixture just until blended.
Pat into greased round 8-inch layer pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Split shortcake while warm. Fill and top with peaches.
Blend sour cream and a 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Serve with shortcake.

title: quickie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise.
Dice bananas and layer on Twinkies. Put Cool Whip on top and add pecans.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Prepare rice.
Serve beef over rice.
Garnish with tomatoes, sour cream, shredded Cheddar cheese and tortilla chips.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water; stir until dissolved.
Add juice and oranges and sherbet.
Chill till set.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Cut loaf in half lengthwise. Combine tomato paste, Parmesan cheese, onion, oregano, salt and 1/8 tsp. pepper. Add meat; mix well. Spread on each loaf halves. Place on baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven; top with tomato slices and green pepper rings. Sprinkle cheese over tomatoes. Bake for 5 minutes.

title: mandel skorpor(swedish rusks)
directions: Cream the butter and cream until very light.
Add beaten egg and flour which has been sifted with baking powder.
Add milk and flavoring. Work together well.
Spread in 2 bread pans (flat loaves).
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Cut in oblong strips while warm and place in oven with heat off to dry.

title: mom's caramel corn
directions: Pour popped popcorn into a large pan (turkey roaster).
You can add pecan pieces of Spanish peanuts to popcorn.
Boil for 5 minutes the butter, brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Take off of fire. Add the vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn and stir thoroughly. Bake at 220° for several hours.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery 6 minutes and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix all together.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes. Last few minutes, cover with a crispy cereal and brown.

title: good vegetable bake
directions: Cook cauliflower and broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Cut up any large pieces; combine both cans of drained corn.
Stir in cheese and soup.
Fold in cooked veggies and mushrooms in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss onion rings with melted butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower-tomato salad
directions: Cut the cauliflower and broccoli flowerets into bite size pieces.
Steam cauliflower pieces 5 minutes and broccoli pieces 5 minutes.
Marinate both overnight in the dressing.
Add the tomatoes just before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar; cut in Crisco. Stir together water, vinegar and egg; mix dry and wet together. Chill 15 minutes before rolling out. Freezes well. Makes 2 double crusts or 4 single crusts.

title: delicious cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine first five ingredients and shape into meatballs. Brown meatballs in shortening.
Remove meatballs from skillet and place into a saucepan.
Add 1 small jar of Ragu meat-flavored spaghetti sauce and 2 small jars of whole mushrooms.

title: brunch bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add egg, milk and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add cheese, ham, garlic and parsley. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish for 40 minutes or bake in miniature muffin tins for 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen muffins.

title: irish soda bread
directions: *Margarine can be used in place of butter.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Wash and separate cauliflower and broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and put in covered dish and refrigerate.
Stir before serving.

title: apple milk punch
directions: Blend ingredients together and serve.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together the sugar, syrup and water.
Boil until it forms a
ball
in
cold
water
when tested.
Beat egg whites. Pour in mixture
a little at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Pour on
buttered wax paper.
Spread with peanut butter, then roll like a jelly roll and slice.
Do not put in icebox.

title: pepper hash
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Let stand at least 1 hour to "marry" flavors.
Refrigerate.
The longer the better.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Combine
all ingredients and pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water; drain.
Put in Pyrex dish with butter.
Mix eggs, milk and water.
Add noodles, cheese and salt to taste.
Sprinkle pepper on top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Drain beans and wash through sieve.
Mix well.

title: tenderloin
directions: Mix all marinade ingredients together.
Marinate tenderloin for several hours, turning occasionally.
Cook on charcoal grill over medium coals (about 6 inches above coals) for 30 to 45 minutes (medium-rare).
Tenderloin should be mopped with marinade and turned about 3 times.

title: kitty litter cake
directions: Make cake mixes according to package directions.
Make pudding according to package directions.
Crumble cookies as small as possible.
Set aside all except 1/4 cup.
To the 1/4 cup cookie crumbs, add a few drops of food coloring and mix with fork or shake in jar.
Crumble cooled cakes into large bowl and mix with half the remaining cookie crumbs and the chilled pudding.
You may not need all the pudding; you don't want it soggy, just moist.
Gently combine.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake until cheese melts at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: rhubarb yum-yum
directions: Combine boiling water, granulated sugar and cornstarch; cook until thick and clear.
Cool.
Melt oleo and mix with brown sugar, flour, oatmeal and cinnamon.
Put 1/2 crumbs in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put diced rhubarb over crumbs.
Pour cornstarch mixture over crumbs and rhubarb.
Sprinkle remainder of crumbs over and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pastry puffs
directions: To cooked and chilled French vanilla pudding, add whipped cream. Mix and refrigerate.
Fill puffs with a pastry bag.
Top with a chocolate glaze.
Bite size eclairs!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake first 6 ingredients 15 minutes; stir.
Bake 20 minutes more, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Crush stack of Ritz crackers on top. Pour another stick of margarine over top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water, then use Tang or orange juice instead of cold water.
Combine all other ingredients and chill overnight.

title: potato-ham salad
directions: In large bowl, blend soup, water, vinegar and pepper.
Add potatoes, ham, pickle and onion.
Chill.
Garnish with egg and parsley.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: party punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Chip and serve with Sprite, ginger ale or 7-Up (one 2 liter bottle).

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers and vinegar in blender and chop.
Put into saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 4 minutes.	Remove from heat and cool for 2 minutes.
Strain.
Add 3 drops of red or green food coloring.
Add Certo.	Pour into sterilized jars and seal. Serve over cream cheese with crackers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put vegetables and water chestnuts in casserole dish. Mix together the soup, sour cream, seasoned salt and water. Pour over vegetables. Top with Ritz cracker crumbs mixed with margarine. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mamaw's soup(healthy and kids love it!)
directions: Brown turkey; add onion after browned.
Add tomato sauce and beans (having been whizzed in blender until smooth).
Add chili powder.
Cook 15 minutes, then add enough water to get 1/2 pot. (I use a Dutch oven-style pot.) Bring to boil, then add the elbow macaroni.
Cook on medium until macaroni is done.
(It's really grandma's mild chili with the beans pureed.)

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat oil in deep fryer or large skillet until it is very hot but don't burn it.
Mix all the ingredients and pour through a funnel held over the hot oil.
Move the funnel in a circle and then crisscross motion as you pour the batter through the funnel to form the cakes.
They rise fast and get pretty large, so be careful not to pour too much batter at a time.

title: old fashioned brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken 2 to 3 hours until tender.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into cubes.
Blend flour and water and add to broth, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add lima beans, corn and tomatoes to broth.
Then add chicken, potatoes, salt and pepper. Heat and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Trim pastry to 1/2 inch beyond edge.
Flute edge.
Prick pastry.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine all ingredients in cocktail shaker, shake well.
Serve in cups.
Sprinkle top with freshly grated nutmeg.
Serves 2.

title: hamburger patties
directions: Mix meat, onion, salt, garlic, egg and crackers up in a large pan.
Make into patties and place in pan.
Drip mushroom soup over each pattie.
Cook in oven at 350° until done.

title: fricassee de pollo chicken cuban style
directions: Cook the chicken with all the ingredients for 25 minutes then add the potatoes and cook 20 more minutes.

title: angel crisps cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and coconut.
Form into balls the size of walnuts. Dip top half in water, then in granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down in center with fingers.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers and onions in pan or crock with salt. Let set for 1 hour.
Rinse them and add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric powder.
Boil all ingredients until peel turns yellow, about 40 minutes.
Pack pickles in hot jars. Close and process in hot bath for 5 minutes.
Start counting after the water returns to boiling.

title: spoon bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add other ingredients in order listed. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use. Drop by tablespoons into greased muffin tin. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Combine cream, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix milk with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Add to cream-butter mixture. Fold in coconut and pecans.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.

title: sausage-vegetable chowder
directions: In a large saucepan melt butter or margarine over low heat. Blend in flour, salt, onion powder, dill weed and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Cut the partially thawed frozen vegetables into bite-size pieces, if necessary.
Stir the vegetables, corn and sausage into the soup.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy crock-pot steak
directions: Mix steak strips with dry onion soup and put in crock-pot. Mix soup with water and pour over steak and cook on low 8 hour. Serve over noodles or rice.
(Add a can of mushrooms, if desired.)

title: german sour cream twists
directions: Sift flour and salt together; cut in shortening (as for pie crust).
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir into flour mixture with sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cover with a damp cloth and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll out dough on sugar.
Roll out oblong about 1/4 inch thick.
Fold dough up from each short side to middle; roll out again and repeat once again.
Cut into 1 x 4-inch strips.
Twist and put on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: macho nacho fever
directions: Lay chips in a shallow pan; sprinkle Cheddar and Jack cheese over chips; sprinkle chopped scallions and peppers over this; spread salsa over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: joycelle's poor man's filet mignon
directions: Mix meat, oatmeal and seasonings.
Form into 6 to 8 patties. Wrap a strip of bacon around each pattie and secure with a toothpick.
Brush top of each pattie with liquid smoke.
Grill until well done.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: jalapeno cornbread(makes 12 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into greased 9 x 16-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Beat eggs slightly in bowl.
Add cheese, parsley, salt, pepper, onion, garlic and oregano.
Mix and then add Bisquick, oil and grated zucchini.
Mix well.
Pour into greased (Crisco) 9 x 9-inch pan or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until slightly brown.
Check after 30 minutes.

title: crawfish enchiladas
directions: In a large skillet, melt 1 stick of butter.
Add the onion, green chilies, green pepper, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 3/4 teaspoon pepper, 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 1/4 teaspoon oregano and garlic.
Saute over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring often. Stir in the cream and bring to a rapid boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add sour cream and beat with a metal whisk until dissolved, about 3 minutes.
Add 3 cups cheese and stir until melted; set aside.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine meat, celery, bread crumbs, egg, salt and onion. Shape into oval patties 1 inch thick.
Brown in butter, on both sides, in skillet.
Pour soup mixed with water over patties and simmer on low heat 30 minutes.
You can also substitute cream of celery or cream of mushroom soup for cream of turkey soup.

title: butter cookies(tastes like sand tarts)
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Then add water.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 325° to 350° about 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add grated zucchini and vanilla. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well and add 1/2 cup raisins (optional).
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: chocolate coconut drops
directions: In top of double boiler over boiling water, melt chocolate chips.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill until firm.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Roll dough into meatball size balls.
Bake at 350° on a greased cookie sheet until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost cookies.
Sprinkle sprinkles of you desire.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix egg, milk, salt and bread crumbs; allow to soften. Thoroughly combine with ground chuck and chopped vegetables. Shape into loaf and place in a slow cooker.
Top with ketchup and green pepper rings.
Place potatoes at the sides of loaf.
(If potatoes are peeled, coat with butter to keep from darkening.) Cover and set to high for 1 hour, then turn to low for 8 to 9 hours.

title: walnut streusel muffinswoodland park, colorado
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in margarine to form crumbs.
Measure 3/4 c. of crumbs with 1/4 c. nuts and set aside. To remaining crumb mixture add the next 7 ingredients.
Combine milk and eggs and stir into dry ingredients just to moisten.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Wash roaster. Place in oblong crock-pot with about 2 cups water. Cook on slow or low for about 8 hours until tender (overnight). Pour broth from roaster into large mixing bowl. Add all other ingredients. Mix good. If too thick, add chicken broth. Mixture should be loose enough to pour. Bake in oblong greased baking dish for 1 hour or until golden brown. After dressing is done, place roaster on top. Serve hot.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Mix the sugar, cornstarch and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook and stir in double boiler until thick.
Add small amount of hot mixture to eggs; stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; chill.
Pour into cooled, baked shell.
Cover with strawberries.
Chill.
Spread with sweetened whipped cream just before serving or spread with Cool Whip when cooled.

title: mexican sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion; drain well.
Combine the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Remove centers from hard rolls and fill with meat mixture.
Roll in foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 dozen hot and tasty sandwiches; a real crowd pleaser.

title: luscious cereal cheese cups(makes 10 servings.)
directions: Line muffin pans with baking cups. Combine flour, cereal and brown sugar in a bowl. Add melted butter and mix until crumbly in texture. Reserve 3/4 cup of the cereal mixture and press the remainder into paper cups, about 2 tablespoons each. Mix Ricotta cheese and sugar until smooth. Stir in egg and lemon juice. Measure about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture into each cup, then sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned and firm.

title: mom's vinegar pie
directions: Combine in a saucepan:
apple cider vinegar, flour, water, salt and lemon extract.
Beat egg yolks and blend with ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly while mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Beat eggs
and milk together;
add rest of ingredients, except vanilla.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Take off heat and add vanilla.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up hen and cover good with water.
Boil until tender. Keep covered with water so as to have plenty of broth for dumplings.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Make a well and pour in milk and melted lard or oil.
Stir together.

title: pizza
directions: Flaten the bread and put it on a pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash, pare and slice raw potatoes.
Arrange in layers in a greased baking dish.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Wash each piece and drain well. Combine flour, herb-blend, paprika and pepper.
Place in paper or plastic bag and add 3 pieces of chicken at a time; shake to coat. Beat eggs, milk, mustard and rosemary together until smooth; set aside.
Combine bread crumbs and parsley.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, shake off excess, then dip in crumb mixture to coat evenly.
Place coated pieces on shallow, lightly greased baking pans.
Let stand 30 minutes before baking.
(Or cover and refrigerate until baking time.)
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake an additional 25 minutes or until browned and juices run clear when knife is inserted.
Serve chilled. Makes 10 generous servings.

title: shrimp puffs
directions: Out of white bread, cut circles about 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Toast under broiler on both sides.

title: mom and me lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, pork sausage with chopped onion and garlic. Add chopped green pepper.
Drain mixture.
Combine tomato paste with 2 cups water.
Whisk until blended.
Pour into meat mixture. Add 1 can tomato sauce, leaf oregano, black pepper to taste. Simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: *sweet bread
directions: Heat milk. Add melted butter and margarine.
Add sugar and oil.
Stir to dissolve.
Add beaten eggs and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Add to above.
Stir
and knead in flour. Depending on day, may need a little more flour.
Place in greased bowl and turn. Cover.
Let rise.
Punch down.
Let rise again. Form into loaves.
Let rise again.
Brush on the glaze (2 eggs, beaten) and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: waldorf-astoria red flannel cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter.
Mix coloring with cocoa; add to mixture.
Add buttermilk with salt alternately with flour.
Add vanilla; add soda and vinegar.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) pans.
Put cake in refrigerator after cool (overnight).

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Place all ingredients, except barbecue sauce, in medium size bowl.
Spray a glass 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients in bowl very well.
Chill for an hour.
Then form into small balls.
Lay in greased pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or you can fry balls in a no-stick pan.

title: thanksgiving hot dish
directions: Put raw hamburger in 9 x 13-inch pan, pat down slightly.
Boil until tender 1 cup water, celery and onion.
Pour this over 1 box croutons and add celery soup and 2 cans chicken soup.
Pour this all over hamburger and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes. Cut into squares and serve.

title: italian chicken
directions: Brown chicken and then place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute mushrooms in margarine and pour over chicken.
Pour broth on top. Place slices of cheese over top to cover.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.

title: vegetable casserole almondine
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling bag as directed.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water to medium firm.
Drain.
Partially open bag of vegetables, drain butter sauce into a small frying pan and saute onion and celery.
Add cooked noodles and mixed vegetables.
Add tomato sauce and sour cream.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with almonds.
(I stir a few into the mixture.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° in oven until brown, about 1 hour.
Serve plain or with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with spoon or mixer. Serve with your favorite fresh vegetables.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onions and green pepper
in drippings. Combine sauteed vegetables, beans, ketchup, molasses, brown sugar and drippings in a greased baking dish.
Mix well.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 1 to 2 hours.
Serves 25 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: apple cake surprise
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and cinnamon together. Spread about 1/4 c. of the crumb mixture on the bottom of a buttered deep 10 inch cake pan.
Separate eggs and beat yolks well.
Add milk, lemon juice, rind and applesauce to beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into milk mixture. Pour into the cake pan.
Cover with remaining graham cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° degrees for 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 stuffing with ingredients; pour into casserole dish. Put remaining stuffing on top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: breaded mushrooms
directions: Cut mushrooms in half; disregard stems (optional).
Wash mushrooms and place in a bowl.
Coat all mushrooms with flour until covered. Melt margarine in frying pan, then add mushrooms. (You will need enough margarine to keep the mushrooms moist while frying.)
Fry the mushrooms until browned and add soy sauce to taste.
Empty the mushrooms into a microwave dish and cook on High for approximately 5 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: amish sweet and sour dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except Crisco oil in a blender.
Blend well.
Slowly add the Crisco oil (or it will separate).

title: easy carrot-nut loaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Add dry ingredients; mix at low speed until just blended.
Fold in carrots and pecans.

title: wet batter
directions: Mix well, then add enough of your favorite beer to obtain the right consistency.
For fish, frog legs, deer, etc.

title: (decadent) chocolate pie
directions: Melt sugar, milk, cream and margarine.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add chocolate.
Place in a large bowl of ice water to cool down (10 minutes).
Pour in mixing bowl and mix on medium for 1 minute.
Pour in crust and chill for 4 hours.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.
Add beets.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1/2 tablespoon sugar to hot milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening; cool.
Add egg, yeast and flour.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick. Spread warm butter; sprinkle sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Put in deep loaf pan and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Layer carrots and cheese slices in a 2 quart casserole.
Saute onion in oleo.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add pepper and celery salt.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350° after pouring over carrots and cheese.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Cook roast until it shreds easily (a crock-pot works well). Mix tomato sauce and taco seasoning with either type cooked beef. Simmer about 15 minutes on stove or in crock-pot until ready to use.
Spoon meat into tortillas.
Roll and place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in a large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Layer in long greased baking dishes (two 13 x 9 x 2-inch); 1 layer of noodles on bottom, pour sauce over noodles, 1 layer of cottage cheese mixture, 1 layer of Mozzarella.
Set aside enough Mozzarella for the top to be added the last 5 to 10 minutes of baking.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen and baked later.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Cover eggs with the beets, sugar and vinegar.
Refrigerate. Make the day ahead.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Add one egg to cake mix, mix thoroughly.
Then fold in whipped topping.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until light brown.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water, adding pineapple and bananas.
Cover the top with miniature marshmallows.
Chill in refrigerator until congealed.

title: laurine's out of this world candy
directions: In a large bowl, mix powdered sugar, butter, Eagle Brand milk, coconut and pecans.
Mix together real good.
Dip hands in additional powdered sugar to keep mixture from sticking to hands. Roll mixture into approximately 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: chicken-vegetable casserole
directions: Cook
slightly
frozen vegetables and drain.
Mix cream of chicken
soup
with sour cream.
Pour over chicken, onions and vegetables.
Place
in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Top with mixture of crushed crackers, sesame seed and melted
oleo.
Bake
at
for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly hot.
Great for a covered dish dinner.

title: raisin fill cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs then other ingredients and flour enough to roll.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti. Combine all ingredients (reserving 1/2 cheese). Place in casserole; top with cheese. Heat at 350° until hot and bubbly. Serves 10.

title: stovetop shepherd's pie(preparation time - 15 minutes; cooking time - 20 minutes)
directions: In 10-inch oven safe skillet cook turkey, onion and chili powder over medium-high heat until turkey is cooked through and onion is tender, stirring to break up turkey.
Stir in half the soup, the water and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes.
Combine potatoes, Cheddar cheese, green onion and remaining soup in medium size bowl.
Spoon over meat mixture (using ice cream scoop), making 5 mounds.
Cover skillet handle with foil to protect from heat.
Broil 6 inches from heat until potatoes begin to brown, 3 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chili bake
directions: Soften corn tortillas in hot oil for a few seconds on each side.
Set aside. In large saucepan, mix remaining ingredients (except cheese) and simmer for 20 minutes. Layer tortillas, soup mixture and cheese and repeat. Bake in 350 oven for 20 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together and cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Mix together and add the rest.
Roll into small balls, about 3/4-inch.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, spaced well apart.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes. Makes about 120 cookies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Coat vegetables with mayonnaise. Add cheddar cheese and mix well. Sprinkle crackers over top and add a couple small dabs of butter on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: streusel bran muffins
directions: In a small bowl, combine the 3 tablespoons flour and the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Using pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside for topping.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Melt butter
in
saucepan.
Add other ingredients; stir constantly until it comes
to a boil.
This will ice 2 layers. Double ingredients for 3 layers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime icebox pudding
directions: Chill evaporated milk overnight.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
When mixture congeals, stir in 1/2 cup of sugar. Whip until fluffy.
In a large bowl, whip chilled evaporated milk, lemon juice and rind.
Add gelatin mixture. Beat thoroughly until fluffy.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with mixture of 5 to 6 graham crackers mixed with 2 tablespoons of sugar.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring, then alternate adding flour and whipping cream.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: best ever baked chicken
directions: Cut breast in half and lay flat.
Place 1 slice of Swiss cheese and 1 slice of dried beef on top of each half of breast and roll up, secure with toothpick.
After this dot with butter.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika on top.
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients. Form into 1-inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet, until golden brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: plant food
directions: Rubbing alcohol will remove ball point pen ink marks.

title: beet relish
directions: Drain beets.
In small saucepan, mix liquid from beets with sugar, vinegar, cloves and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Mix beets with beans and onion and pour hot liquid over them.
Refrigerate, covered, for several hours or overnight.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: skor bars(candy)
directions: Heat butter and brown sugar to 308° on candy thermometer (hard crack) over medium heat.
Pour caramel layer over pecans that are placed in single layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top; spread as they melt.
Cool for 3 to 4 hours.
Flip out of pan and break into pieces.

title: whiskey sour punch
directions: Twenty-five minutes before serving:
Thinly slice orange, discard ends.
With small sharp knife, flute edges of each slice; set aside.
In punch bowl, combine undiluted lemonade concentrate and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Garnish with orange slices. Makes 16 cups.

title: tomato-shrimp saute
directions: In a large nonstick skillet over medium high heat, warm half of the oil until hot but not smoking.
Add the zucchini and garlic and saute until golden, about 4 minutes.
Add the roasted red pepper and the red pepper flakes and cook for 1 minute.
Add the remaining oil, the shrimp, thyme, pepper and salt.
Cook shrimp mixture, stirring occasionally until shrimp turn pink and are barely cooked, 3 to 6 minutes.
Gently stir in tomatoes and olives and cook until the shrimp are opague throughout and the tomatoes are heated through, about 2 minutes.
Great over pasta.

title: vegetable-stuffed meat cups(microwave main dish)
directions: Place vegetables in small microwave-safe bowl.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Add 1/2 cup of the cheese; toss to mix well. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine beef, soup mix, egg, bread crumbs and ketchup; mix well.
Divide meat mixture into 8 equal parts.
Press into bottoms and up sides of eight 6 ounce custard cups or individual casseroles.
Divide vegetable mixture among meat cups.
Arrange 4 custard cups in a circle in the microwave oven. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 4 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, rearranging cups once during cooking.
Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon of the remaining cheese.
Let stand, covered, while cooking remaining cups.
Repeat cooking for remaining cups. Makes 8 servings.

title: pheasant or chicken with creamy sauce
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Rinse pheasant/chicken breasts and pat dry.
Cut each into 6 to 8 pieces. Coat each piece with mayonnaise/yogurt and roll in crumb mixture. Place pheasant/chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Drizzle margarine on top.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until tender.
Serve with sauce.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until the sugar dissolves. Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs. Add milk and stir with a fork until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Knead just until smooth.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately, then add raisins and nuts (sprinkle raisins and nuts with flour).
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Put topping on cake while cake is hot.
Punch holes in cake and spoon topping on.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Grill, broil or pan-fry chicken until cooked through.
Slice crosswise.
Combine chicken and vegetables in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl, mix well.
Pour over salad. Mix gently.
Chill, occasionally stirring gently and serve on lettuce-lined platter.
Use remaining Pace sauce to season to taste.
Serves 4.

title: mop sauce for chicken or steak
directions: Mix and
bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
(It will keep weeks in refrigerator.)

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as directed on box (can add some nuts).
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Heath bars can be crushed in package then removed from package and placed in a bowl.
Layer as follows in large compote or large pan (the compote lets you see the layers):
Crumble 1/2 of brownies on bottom of container.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over brownies.
Sprinkle with Heath bars and pecans.
Next use 1/2 large container of Cool Whip.
Continue to layer the remaining 1/2 crumbled brownies, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 Cool Whip, 1/2 Heath bars and 1/2 pecans.
Decorate top with whole pecans and some chocolate stars by Brach.
Can also grate stars for a light dusting of chocolate.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Place all ingredients together in one bowl.
Beat 20 minutes with electric mixer.
Grease and flour a deep tube pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: good baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook in 400° oven.

title: fresh broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, covered in small amount of boiling water, until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and chop coarsely.
In large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Blend in flour; add water, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly.
Add chopped broccoli. Bring to boiling and stir in cheese until melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: swiss chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 1 slice cheese on each breast.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken and cheese. Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Crumble over chicken.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: happy home*******
directions: "Anything is possible but nothing is easy."

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place a skillet in the oven with 2 tablespoons oil in it and leave until grease is real hot.
Mix dry ingredients together, then add the egg and enough milk to mix to make it smooth.
Pour in the hot grease and stir and pour into skillet and bake 20 minutes.

title: peach crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Measure 3/4 cup of this mixture and set aside.
Press remaining mixture over bottom and 3/4 up sides of nine-inch spring-form pan.
Bake crust at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix peaches, 1/2 cup sugar, tapioca and lemon juice.
Arrange in bottom of crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with rest of flour mixture and continue baking for 20 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serve warm or cold with favorite topping.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well using hand.
Shape into balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
May be frozen and used for snacks later.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Add all the cans of vegetables except creamed corn.
Rinse each can with 1/2 can of water and add.
Cook about 30 minutes and add creamed corn the last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cream of tartar for 5 minutes.
Drop crackers one at a time in boiling mixture.
Do not stir! Keep boiling.
Boil 2 minutes.
Make regular pastry shell.
Put in the filling.
Dot with butter and 1 teaspoon brown sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put on the top crust.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: golden pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water; let stand until mixture starts to gel.
Add drained pineapple and diced orange to gelatin; stir.
When set cut and place on lettuce leaf; garnish with unsweetened Bing cherry.
Yield:
5 servings.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories 28, One serving = 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine milk and soup, stir well.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Cook corkscrews for 7 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain again.
Put remaining ingredients in a blender. Blend until smooth.
Pour over drained macaroni and let marinate overnight.
In the morning add broccoli flowerets, bite-size pieces of bell pepper and 5 carrots, sliced on a slant.
Let all marinate for at least 5 hours.
Lastly, garnish with hard-boiled egg slices.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add mashed bananas and beaten eggs, one at a time.
Mix well; then add vanilla, dry ingredients and pecans.
Pour
into
well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for
45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool 1 minute before removing from pan.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Simmer beans and ham bone 2 hours.
Add mashed potatoes and other ingredients.
Simmer until all ingredients are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove ham bone and chip meat.

title: granny ward's ginger cookies
directions: Mix together well the shortening, brown sugar and molasses, then stir in the cold water.
Sift together and stir in the flour and spices.
Stir in 2 teaspoons of soda, dissolved in 3 tablespoons of cold water.
Chill dough.
Roll out very thick (1/2 inch).
Place far apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 7 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Toss with Italian dressing.
Chop tomato, cucumber and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients together. Best if refrigerated for a few hours before serving.

title: dirt cake
directions: In separate bowl, mix milk and pudding.
Add to creamed mixture and mix in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies and pudding mix, ending with cookies.
Refrigerate.
Yummy!!!!!

title: mom's dutch pickles
directions: Soak overnight in salt and water.
Drain in the morning.
Use a cup of vinegar to mix flour and sugar.
Add other ingredients. Boil for 30 minutes in a quart of vinegar.
Can in clean, hot jars.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a large pot.
Add potatoes and broccoli and cook 10 minutes, then add chicken soup and Velveeta cheese.
Cook until cheese melts and soup reaches serving temperature.

title: tasty cubed potatoes
directions: *Green onion flakes are in the seasoning section (spices can be hard to find).

title: hamburger hash
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain. Add onion and potatoes; cook until tender. Add green beans and salt and pepper. Cook a little longer until very hot. Eat.

title: taco appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with taco seasoning.
Spread out on a plate. Pour salsa on top.
Mix other ingredients and put on top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: martha's chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken broth with soup; mix well.
Place butter in casserole; layer chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, eggs and vinegar and mix well.
Add coconut, pecans and raisins and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and chill.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add strawberries.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Chill until jelled a little.
Put in mold in layers of jello and sour cream.
Set.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Put 1/2 in bottom of casserole. Mix squash, carrots and onion and add to casserole.
Mix sour cream and
soup;
pour over the vegetables.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: Combine beef, pork, rice, sugar, onion, salt and pepper.
Wilt cabbage leaves by placing in boiling water for a few minutes. Place about 1/2 cup of mixture in each cabbage leaf and roll up securely.
Place rolls in baking pan.
Dot each with butter. Combine water and soup; pour over rolls.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana balls
directions: Blend together the Cool Whip, sugar and sour cream.
Cut bananas into bite-size pieces.
Coat with the mixture and roll in flaked coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed, except nuts, in a large casserole dish.
Microwave 4-5 minutes on high until boiling.
Mix with electric mixer on high till well blended.
Add nuts and pour into pan sprayed with Pam.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Use an 8x8 baking dish. Cut up butter in baking dish and place in oven to melt butter. Mix Bisquick, milk, egg, and sugar together. Pour in baking dish over the melted butter. Pour fruit over the mixture. Bake in oven at 350 degrees for approx. 45 minutes.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli; combine eggs, onion, soup and mayonnaise. Place layer of broccoli in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add layer of cheese.
Pour small amount of sauce on top.
Repeat layers until all used.
Top with stuffing and sprinkle with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef tips 'n gravy
directions: Cook
beef
stew until tender.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drain mushrooms and place on top of beef.
Place onions and
pepper
on top.
Prepare gravy mix as directed on package. Pour
over
beef and vegetables.
Cover with plastic wrap
and microwave
for
to 5 minutes or until pepper and onions are tender.

title: rio grande dip
directions: Combine avocados, lemon juice, pepper and salt.
Combine taco seasoning, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Combine bean dip and salsa.

title: baked southwestern dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut a 1/4-inch slice from top of bread; set aside. Remove center from bread, leaving a 1/2-inch thick shell. Cut center of bread in 1-inch cubes.
Bake until toasted, about 5 minutes.
With an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese, sour cream and salsa until smooth. Stir in cheese. Spoon into bread shell.
Place reserved slice on top. Wrap in foil. Bake until hot, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with toasted bread cubes and fresh vegetables.

title: special cherry salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Drain cottage cheese. Place all in a bowl.
Add Cool Whip and gelatin.
Chill.

title: scalloped cabbage and ham
directions: Cook cabbage, covered, in boiling salted water for about 10 minutes. Drain. Melt butter or margarine in saucepan; blend in flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper. Stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and boils. Add cheese and onion and cook until cheese melts. Place drained cabbage in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Add diced ham and pour sauce over all. Mix well with a fork and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly and brown. Serves 6.

title: microwave pizza casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Combine ground beef, green pepper and onion in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole, cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Fold back a corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 5 minutes or until done, stirring at 2 minute intervals; drain.
Add noodles, pizza sauce and next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Cover and microwave at High 17 to 19 minutes, stirring at 6 minute intervals.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix above together. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hominy-bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish, sprinkling hot pepper sauce over the top.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes, then uncover and bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo, sugar and nuts.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk. Spread over first layer.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: granny oyzort's fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add diced apples and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Bake in an 18 1/2 x 11-inch pan until brown and springy to touch.

title: ugly cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, butter and eggs.
Pat into greased and floured cake pan.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: In a large Dutch oven, put 1 cup rice, 1 can of tomato sauce, 1/4 cup water and 1/2 of the ground meat (raw).
Salt and pepper. Add onion, green pepper, corn, 1 can tomato sauce, 1/4 cup water and the other 1/2 of the meat.
Salt and pepper.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° with lid on for 1 hour.
Remove lid and bake until bacon is brown.

title: granny's coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Cook on top of stove until thick, stirring constantly.
After thick, add vanilla and coconut.
Pour in already baked pie crust.

title: chilironi
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with the onions and the green pepper.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer for a time.
Add the can of kidney beans and the macaroni which has been cooked and drained.
Heat throughout.

title: melon cooler salad(serves 8)
directions: Place Neufchatel cheese and concentrate in food processor or blender container.
Process until well blended.
Spoon melon balls into parfait glasses or into individual bowls (8).
Top with cream cheese mixture.

title: egg white omelet
directions: Use cauliflower, broccoli, onions, peppers, green tomatoes or any firm vegetables.
Use pre-mix pancake mix.
Mix according to directions and add seasoning salt.
Dig veggies in pancake batter; drop into hot oil and cook until brown.
Enjoy.

title: sweet and sour meat balls(appetizer)
directions: Heat chili sauce and grape jelly to boiling point.
Mix meat with seasonings.
Add egg and crackers which have been soaked in water and squeeze nearly dry.
Make real tiny meatballs and put in boiling sauce.
Cool slowly over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add melted butter and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each.
Add milk, vanilla and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Then mix lemon jello, lemon juice, water and food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture.
Whip the frozen milk until like whipped cream.
Slowly stir into the lemon and sugar mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
You can put Dream Whip on top or crushed graham crackers.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Add salad dressing to desired consistency.

title: alaskan igloo
directions: Soften liverwurst (mash).
Chop onion very fine and mix with liverwurst.
Coat inside of round bowl very thinly with mayonnaise.
Put mixture in bowl and refrigerate until cold. Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Remove liverwurst from bowl and put on plate flat-side down.
Cover igloo with cream cheese using a spatula.
Slice olives and press into igloo gently. Serve with crackers and small serving knife.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with cornflakes; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Heat oven to 423 degrees.
Wash cabbage, chop into small pieces.
Cook 10 minutes in 1 cup of water.
Stir often.
Will be slightly cooked - set aside.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time; beat well. Add remaining ingredients alternately with milk.
Make three 9-inch layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and taco mix,
mixing well.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13 -inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed. Serve with chips.
Yield 8 cups.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Fry onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and soup; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through and serve over noodles.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in butter in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth. Gradually add water and wine, stirring until blended.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add shrimp and simmer 5 minutes or until shrimp are pink.

title: turkey potato patties
directions: Combine and form into cakes.
Brown in pan with small amount of oil or non-stick spray.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat
sugar,
oil,
vanilla
and
eggs	together
until fluffy; add cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add flour and mix until blending.
Add zucchini, raisins and walnuts and mix. Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sunday afternoon screwdriver
directions: Chill orange juice prior to putting into thermos.
Serve with maraschino cherries or orange slices.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: sauteed turkey medallions with mustard and tarragon
directions: Saute turkey slices in olive oil 2 minutes on each side to seal in juices.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Saute shallots until soft.
Add wine, chicken stock and garlic; bring to boil.
Reduce to 1/2 cup.
Whisk in cream and mustard; bring to boil.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add tarragon, thyme, salt and pepper.
Return turkey to pan with juices and cook until warmed through.
Serve over bed of rice or pasta.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole.
If desired, add Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Combine first six ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Add eggplant and mushrooms.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set. Yields 8 servings.

title: calico salad
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil and cool until warm. Put the next 3 ingredients in a colander and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing over the vegetables.
Mix well.
Will keep for 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: clouds in sky salad
directions: Mix all together except Jell-O.
Sprinkle Jell-O in and mix.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and arrange in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in Cool Whip. Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix and pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Yields 2 pies.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Bring broccoli to a boil.
Cook, covered, for 6 minutes.
Add cheese and margarine; let melt.
Pour into a casserole dish. Add remaining ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
(Cut chicken into small pieces.)
Divide in half for a smaller casserole.

title: chess cake
directions: This will make 2 pies.
Use a cookie recipe for the crusts. Roll out pretty thin.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Knead above ingredients into dough until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth or wax paper and place in covered bowl in the refrigerator.
(This dough may be stored 3 to 4 days.)

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 small pies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients once.

title: tangy low-fat baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken.
Pat dry.
Combine red and black pepper.
Rub over chicken.
Combine salad dressing, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Lightly brush both sides of chicken with some of the dressing mixture.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Heat remaining sauce to boiling and serve with chicken.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry on a hot griddle.

title: fruit pops
directions: Put all together in blender and mix well. Pour into 5 oz. paper cups and place a stick in each cup and freeze.

title: chocolate cream puffs
directions: Heat water, butter and salt to rolling boil in medium saucepan.
Add flour all at once; stir vigorously until mixture leaves the sides of the pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix with cornbread mix and remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased square pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Mix Jell-O in 3/4 cup hot water.
Beat eggs.
Add Jell-O then flavoring and oil.
Mix until blended.
Add cake mix.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender and falls from bone.
Remove from water.
Add macaroni to broth and cook.
Saute chopped bell pepper and onion in small amount of oil.
Add chopped chicken, onion, pepper, pimentos, English peas and grated cheeses to macaroni. Pour all ingredients into baking dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix oleo, crushed pretzels and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Husk and silk corn.
Wrap each ear in waxed paper.
Twist ends of paper.
Arrange corn on paper towels.
Allow at least 1 inch between ears.
Microcook 1 ear about 2 minutes, 2 ears 3 to 4 minutes, 4 ears 6 to 7 minutes and 6 ears 8 to 10 minutes. Halfway through cooking rearrange corn and turn over or omit wrapping in waxed paper.
Place husked and silked corn in baking dish.
Microcook covered for times listed and rearranging.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in vegetable oil in large saucepan until tender.

title: zucchini skillet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat butter, brown sugar and mustard until melted.
Blend.
