Add zucchini, pepper, onion, tomatoes and salt.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chico's chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat; roll out and crush crackers.
Add to butter.
Set aside.

title: no cook lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.
Real good.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend together Cool Whip and cheese spread.
Add crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Cover and chill 2 or 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: blender egg custard
directions: Blend for 3 minutes. Pour in a 9-inch deep pie dish that has been sprayed with Pam (I use butter flavor) and let stand for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with chopped nuts, coconut or nutmeg, if desired. Bake in a 350° preheated oven for approximately 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: helen's italian bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over 2/3 cup warm water and stir to dissolve yeast, then mix in 6 cups flour, a little at a time; work in enough flour to form a fairly stiff dough.
Knead on a lightly floured board until elastic and smooth, about 8 to 10 minutes. Shape into a ball; place in a large greased bowl, turning to grease all over.

title: chill cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put wax paper in opened cracker box and pour in mixed ingredients.
Close box down and chill 3 days before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat.
Sift flour with soda in it.
Add this and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and mashed bananas last.
Cook this in 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat on high 5 to 7 minutes.
An excellent icing for decorating as well as frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take seasoning mix from Stove Top stuffing and mix with broth. Cook 5 minutes.
Mix soups (both) with this and simmer.
Add chicken.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Add 1/2 package of stuffing crumbs to baking dish.
Pour chicken mixture over crumbs.
Then add remaining crumbs on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: marbled andes brownies
directions: Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare mix and bake as directed.
Remove from oven.
Immediately place unwrapped candies on surface of hot brownies.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes or until candies melt.
Using knife, swirl candies to cover surface of brownies.
Cool until set.
Cut into bars.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Debone and remove skin from chicken.
Beat with tenderizing mallet and salt and pepper.
Place 1 to 2 slices of dried beef in each half of breast and roll with beef inside.
Wrap each chicken breast with strips of bacon and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Mix sour cream, chicken soup and mushroom soup.
Pour over breasts.
Bake for 4 hours on 250°.

title: onion mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mash with milk and butter.
Cook onions.
Brown onions in butter or oil.
Mix into potatoes very well.
Cook in casserole dish, uncovered.
Brush top with egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until top is brown.

title: whiskey date cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat real good; add flour and mix well.
Also add the whiskey, then put the dates in.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken breast in lemon sauce
directions: Cut each chicken breast horizontally, to make two thin slices. Coat with flour. Heat margarine in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Cook chicken and garlic in margarine 4 to 6 minutes, turning once until chicken is brown. Add apple and lemon juice; sprinkle with pepper, heat until hot.

title: melt-in-your mouth sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and mix well.
Add vanilla and mix until blended well.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix until creamy.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and flatten with a small glass dipped in white sugar.
Works better if cool dough in refrigerator for awhile.
Can then roll out with fingers.
Makes nicer and rounder cookies.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes or until brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Add bread crumbs to hot milk.
Cool.
Add other ingredients, then pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Half cup raisins may be added.
Serve with nutmeg sauce or ice cream on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Debone and skin chicken.
Use broth.
Add 2 cans vegetables.
Bring to boil.
Add flour and water to thicken.
Add chicken, stirring well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake until biscuits are browned.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until smooth for about 2 or 2 1/2 minutes.
Bake in
three 8-inch pie pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan which is greased and floured.
Bake according to directions on box of cake mix.
Ice.

title: curried chicken pat
directions: To hard cooked eggs, grated or chopped finely, add mayonnaise, preferably home-made.
Add finely minced fresh chicken, turkey, or fine-quality sliced turkey breast.
Add finely diced celery and green pepper.
Season with curry powder and other seasoning, such as Lawry's or Aromat.
Serve in bowl or spread on white bread rounds, moistened with thousand-island dressing.
Thousand-island dressing is best made with home-made mayonnaise mixed with bottled chile sauce (Bennett's brand, if you can find it).

title: ginger cookies
directions: Add molasses, sugar and eggs to the margarine; beat well. Sift together and add to this mixture the flour, soda and spices. Refrigerate the dough for several hours or overnight.
Make into small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake until firm or brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ingredients; form a loaf.
Place in a shallow pan in moderate oven (350°).
While it is starting to bake, combine the following to make your prize winning tart sweet gravy.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate several hours.
Very good for vegetables and/or chips.

title: penny's potato soup
directions: Combine water and chicken bouillon.
Cook vegetables in water mixture until soft.
Add milk slowly, stirring to combine. Combine flour and sour cream.
Add to soup mixture, stirring slowly.
Lower heat and simmer on low until slightly thickened and ready to serve.

title: quick creamed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 6 boned chicken breasts in a shallow baking dish. Combine and pour over chicken 1 cup canned creamed mushroom soup, 1 cup cultured sour cream and 1/2 cup chopped mushrooms.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour.
Delicious and easy.
Best served with rice.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In large Dutch oven saute sliced peppers and onions in oil until lucid.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on low to medium flame for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve covered with melted cheese, if desired.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add condensed milk and vanilla (1 teaspoon).
Beat until well blended.
Add lime juice; beat.
Pour into crust.
Beat heavy cream, sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla until stiff and peaks form.
Spread over pie.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: easy streusel pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.

title: touch of hawaii salad
directions: Drain tuna but leave in medium size chunks. Rinse with cold water and drain well. Toss lightly with pineapple, green pepper, celery and mayonnaise.
Pile in 1/2 papaya or in lettuce cups. Sprinkle lightly with parsley. Serve on plate with tomatoes, ripe olives and heated French roll.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain; let cool to touch.
Peel and cut into slices; set aside.

title: chicken breasts with raspberry sauce(makes 4 servings)
directions: YOU CAN USE CRAN-RASPBERRY JUICE ALSO.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread out crescent rolls to fit baking sheet or pizza pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 11-13 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool 1 minute.
Slide onto a cooling rack.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, dill weed, and garlic surgery.
Spread evenly over crust.
Then spread mixed vegetables and cheese over top of crust.

title: spanish garlic soup(sopa de ajo)
directions: Trim crusts from bread; cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a large frying pan, melt butter; add garlic and bread cubes and cook over medium heat, stirring often, until bread is lightly browned. Remove from pan; reserve.

title: chicken marinade for bbg
directions: Combine and use to marinate chicken.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
(I divided into 2 pans because too much for a 9 x 13-inch pan.)
Beat egg; add milk and pour over spaghetti.
Brown venison.
Drain off fat.
Add garlic salt and other seasonings.
Spread over spaghetti; add mushrooms and spaghetti sauce over this.
Top with cheese and cover with pepperoni slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (covered with foil first 45 minutes, then remove foil last 15 minutes).
Can be frozen.

title: tea cakes
directions: Melt sugar and butter real good.
Add other ingredients.
Put flour in flour bowl.
Pour ingredients in center of flour.
Work up like biscuits.
When dough gets stiff, pinch off some, roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: daddy's slaw
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in a pan and bring to a boil.
Slowly pour hot mixture over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Let sit about an hour, then you can stir and refrigerate. Will keep for several days.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes side by side in greased casserole.
Pour syrup (see recipe following) over and bake 20 minutes at 400°, basting from time to time with syrup.
Just before serving, place marshmallows on top and return to oven.
Let brown slightly.

title: apple brownie cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over apples and set aside.
Cream 1 cup sugar and Crisco.
Add egg; cream well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until it forms coarse crumbs; add apples, raisins and nuts.
Mix well, pour in floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: nutty nuggets
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Sift flour with salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Then add nuts and vanilla.
Form into small balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool and roll in generous amount of powdered sugar.
Wait 5 more minutes and roll in sugar again.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.

title: easy buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together into a bowl, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add solid vegetable shortening.
With a fork, blend mixture until it resembles coarse meal; then stir in buttermilk. Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface; knead lightly for 4 or 5 strokes.
Roll or pat into a 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick round.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter (or glass).
Place on a baking sheet and bake in a preheated 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: copper carrots(even kids will eat them!)
directions: Peel carrots.
Cut into 1/4-inch diagonal slices.
Blend equal amounts of water and Savannah cinnamon mix to just cover carrots. Cook until tender, but crisp.
Also excellent for sweet potatoes.

title: country style steak
directions: Spray 10-inch cast-iron frying pan with "Pam".
Heat pan with Crisco.
Roll steaks in flour; place in pan.
Salt and pepper. Brown on medium heat; turn over to brown 2nd side.
Remove steak from pan.
Add flour to pan.
Brown flour over over medium heat. Add 4 cups water to flour mixture.
Stir.
Add browned steaks. Cover and simmer on low heat for 60 minutes.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Blend broth into soup in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix in remaining ingredients except almonds.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with almonds.
You may omit the chestnuts and use 1 1/2 cups chopped celery.
Serves 4.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in 8-cup measure.
Add milk and butter. Do not stir!
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir.
Pour onto buttered dish.
Freeze for 20 minutes or refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut and serve.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain the pineapple and cherries.
Mix together the first four ingredients.
Put the lemon juice in last since this is what thickens it up.
Makes 2 to 4 pies (2 thick or 4 thin).
Tastes better chilled.

title: easy brownies from scratch
directions: Melt butter.
In a bowl, mix eggs, sugar and cocoa.
Add butter to this mixture.
Stir.
Add flour; stir.
Add vanilla; stir.
Pour into 8-inch buttered and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and chopped nuts.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Next, mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and milk together and spread over pie.
Top with extra Cool Whip if desired.

title: swiss pancakes
directions: May have to adjust flour and milk for frying consistency, but batter should be thin.
This makes crepe like pancakes.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix together and press into an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients and boil for 5 minutes and let cool or use hot.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix peas, corn, pepper, onions and tomatoes.
Combine with mayonnaise.
Stir together.
Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cranberry sauce and mix well. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in apples and put into a congealed salad mold.
Chill until firm.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let come to a boil.
Allow to sit 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Excellent winter time hot drink.

title: chicken-asparagus casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salt water for 30 to 40 minutes. Arrange asparagus in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer chicken pieces on asparagus.
Mix cream of chicken soup with mayonnaise; pour over chicken.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: applesauce cake - 1935
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove toys from countertop.
Measure 2 cups flour.
Get baking powder.
Remove kids hands from flour. Put flour, baking powder and salt into a sifter.
Vacuum mixture the kids spilled on kitchen floor.
Get an egg. Answer the phone. Separate egg.
Warm baby's bottle.
Help daughter figure math problem.
Grease pan.
Answer the doorbell.
Take 1/2-inch salt from greased pan.
Look for kids.
Put mess in wastebasket. Put dishes in the dishwasher.
Call the bakery. Take an aspirin. Gotcha!!!!!!!

title: strawberry yogurt cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a rectangular pan (13 x 9-inch).
Beat cake mix (dry), water, oil, egg and one container of yogurt in large bowl at low speed, about 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, or until cake springs back when touched in center.
Cool completely.
Fold container of yogurt into whipped topping. Spread over top of cake.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired. Refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: florida steak
directions: Combine ingredients and "pat out" in large pan 3/4-inch thick. Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Cut into squares. Dip in flour and brown in Crisco; season to taste.
Put in roaster and make a gravy by combining drippings, soup and 1 can water.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Flake salmon; add onion, lemon juice, mashed potatoes and mix well.
Form into croquettes desired size and shape and roll in cracker crumbs, dip in slightly beaten egg diluted with water, roll in crumbs again. Fry in oil until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 5 to 6 croquettes.

title: greek recipe dolmades(stuffed grape leaves)
directions: Can use dried seasonings.
Can add 1/2 to 1 pound of cooked ground lamb or beef.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sour cream until smooth.
Add onions and taco seasoning.
Spread on dish as a mold and refrigerate to firm up.
Shred lettuce and layer on top; layer cheeses and top with tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Great for a party!
Always a favorite!

title: 3 layer strawberry dessert
directions: Mix with a fork the pretzels, 4 tablespoons sugar and 3/4 cup oleo.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool completely.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in bowl, tossing to mix.
Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Pour liquid over broccoli mixture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box.
Cool.
Add fruit and berries.
Put half of mixture in cake pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread with sour cream and add remaining jello mixture. Refrigerate until set.
Can be made with raspberries in place of strawberries.

title: frying batter
directions: Open the beer and pour off into a bowl 2 hours before mixing the batter.
Leave uncovered at room temperature.
To prepare the batter, combine all the ingredients in a large mixing bowl and whip at medium-high speed with an electric mixer until frothy and rather thin in texture.
(Or whip vigorously by hand with a whisk, for about 4 minutes.)
Cover the bowl with a plastic wrap and let stand at room temperature for at least 3 hours.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients with a mixer.
Add shrimp and butter, melted.
Mix to chop the shrimp a little.
Pour into a small serving bowl.
Cover and chill.
Serve with sliced bread or crackers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix
pudding and Dream Whip with 1 cup milk; whip well. Add pecans, marshmallows and pineapple.
Mix well.

title: carob fudge
directions: Melt
carob
chips in double boiler until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in other ingredients. Spread into 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate.
When firm, slice into chunks and serve.

title: spinach squares
directions: Slice zucchini into thin coins.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top with dab of margarine and grated Parmesan cheese.
Place under broiler until bubbly.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry supreme
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the sugar and cream cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix together strawberries and strawberry liquid, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Add whipped Cool Whip.
Fold until well blended. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish or 2 smaller dishes. Top with whole or sliced strawberries. Freeze.
Defrost slightly before serving as salad or dessert. Makes approximately 48 servings.

title: hawaiian pineapple pie
directions: Mix ingredients, pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: coconut cream eggs
directions: Combine sugar and butter in bowl.
Add egg white, milk, and vanilla to mixture.
Mix.
Add coconut and mix until mixture can be formed.
Take a small amount of mixture and form into eggs. Put the chocolate chips in a double boiler and melt until smooth. Roll eggs in chocolate until they are evenly coated.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherries or pineapple in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and spread cake mix over fruit; spread melted margarine drizzled over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine chopped chicken, cabbage and green onion tops in a large bowl. Mix well and set aside. Reserve the seasoning packet and place noodles in a bowl and coarsely crush. Stir in seeds and almonds. Melt butter in skillet. Add the mixture of noodles and stir until toasted. In another bowl, combine reserved seasoning packets with sugar, oil, Accent, salt, pepper and vinegar. Toss all three mixtures together.

title: strawberry delight(lo-cal)
directions: Pour juice from pineapple into saucepan.
Heat.
Add Jell-O, stirring until Jell-O dissolves.
Mix yogurt with all other ingredients; add hot gelatin mixture, stirring until well blended. Pour into mold or dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Serves 12.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour, then stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 2 unbaked pie shells for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: Place sugar, water and egg whites in medium-size heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, beating continuously with electric mixer on high speed until soft peaks form. Remove from heat; add marshmallow creme and beat mixture on high speed until stiff peaks form, 2 minutes. Use at once to frost the cake of your choice.

title: microwave christmas fudge
directions: Place evaporated milk, sugar and butter or margarine in a large, microwave-safe bowl.
Mix well.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir every minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients until marshmallows and chips are melted.
Pour mixture into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: fried burritos
directions: Brown chuck; drain all fat off.
Add seasoning mix and water; simmer until liquid is gone.
Add beans and mix well.
Put mixture on tortillas and roll up and deep fry.
Add cheese before rolling up.

title: yukon party spread
directions: Combine salmon, cheese, lemon juice, onion, salt, horseradish and liquid smoke.
Mix and chill several hours.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size chunks (this takes approximately 4 weeks).
Place in large black pot.
Cover with water; add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer over a kerosene fire until tender (about 5 months).
Add potatoes, carrots and onions and cook for about 3 more days.
This serves about 5,000.
If more are expected, add the rabbit, but do so only if necessary, as not too many people like to find a hare in their stew.

title: quiche
directions: Saute 1 tablespoon oil, onion and ham.
Mix in blender the eggs, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Add sauteed items, then add cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in 9 x 9-inch greased dish.

title: mini melts
directions: Lay meat flat on rye bread and cut into 4 sections.
Spread each slice with mustard and top with a slice of meat and cheese. Put into microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender.
Drain well.
Add cracker crumbs, margarine and 1 cup of cheese.
Beat egg with milk; add to mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheddar-onion bundt
directions: Thaw dough, then slice each loaf into 12 equal pieces.
Wrap each piece of dough around cheese.
Combine melted butter, onion soup or garlic powder.
Dip each ball of dough in mixture.
Place pieces in Bundt pan or loaf pan sprayed with Pam, cover.
Let rise until doubled in size, about 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove immediately from pan. Serve warm.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Add strawberries, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into 8 x 13-inch glass dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread sour cream on top.
spoon rest of jello mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate until set.

title: rick's favorite spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Drain fat.
In large pot, boil spaghetti noodles until tender; drain water and keep spaghetti in pot.
Add ground beef, tomato sauce, garlic powder, oregano and chili powder.
You may need to add some water about 1/2 to 1 cup. Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.

title: fannie may fudge
directions: Mix the sugar, milk, vanilla and butter in a large saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil for 2 minutes. Turn off heat.
Add the marshmallows, chocolate chips and chocolate bars.
Stir until melted. Add the nuts.
Pour into buttered jelly roll pan.
(Fudge is creamier when kept at room temperature.)

title: texas hash
directions: In shortening, cook ground beef, onions and green pepper. Stir in tomatoes, either rice or noodles (your choice), chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole; cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover the last 15 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute garlic in margarine. Add shrimp, oregano and salt.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Stir in wine and serve.
Makes 4 servings at about 200 calories.

title: creamy herb pasta salad
directions: Mix the first five ingredients until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly and chill.
Nice served on lettuce.

title: mamaws fried squash
directions: Saute squash, onions, celery and garlic in butter until soft. Add cheese and bread crumbs with seasonings and cook slowly until slightly brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: three lettuce salad
directions: Trim and core lettuce.
Pull leaves apart; rinse well.
Pat dry.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Pour water over meal and sugar mixture until moist.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil.
Cook until brown and crisp, turning once or twice.
You can increase according to how many people you plan to feed.
Be your own judge.
It will melt in your mouth.

title: different stuffed celery
directions: Blend the 3 cheeses, onion and Worcestershire sauce together thoroughly.
Separate stalks of celery and spread each stalk with mixture.
Fit stalks together stuffing to stuffing.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook macaroni in 3 cups boiling salted water in saucepan until tender.
Set aside, covered, for 5 minutes; drain.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter in skillet until golden; set aside.

title: big batch pie crust
directions: Can store in refrigerator (for up to 6 weeks) without water. Should make approximately 15 pie crusts.

title: josephine's pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a 12 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: favorite cole slaw
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add Miracle Whip salad dressing to taste.

title: boston cream fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cream and syrup to 234° (soft ball).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Add pecans. Pour into buttered dish or drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: breakfast delights
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Break up bread to cover bottom.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon sausage over bread and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next morning at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes with no cover.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the first 8 ingredients.
Add other ingredients in order as given.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Pour batter into pan; bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: very easy cookies
directions: Mix together.
Stir in any desired additions.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix in plastic container.
Shake and stir several times a day. Put in glass jar after four days.

title: rhubarb-strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients; let stand for 15 minutes to soften tapioca.
Place bottom pastry in deep dish (9-inch) pie plate.
Add filling.
Top with a lattice crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375°; bake 30 minutes more or until filling is bubbly and rhubarb is tender.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil 6 boneless chicken breasts. Saute bell pepper and onion in butter. Pour Rotel and soups into skillet with sauteed onions and bell peppers. Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste. Heat in skillet until warm and bubbly. Cut boiled chicken into pieces. Take 12 flour tortillas and fill with chicken. Spoon a small amount of sauce over chicken. Roll tortilla and place folded side down in baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over filled tortillas, cover with shredded cheese. Place aluminum foil over baking dish. Bake in oven for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Half recipe for 2 people.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Melt together first 2 ingredients in top of a double boiler. Remove from heat and mix in remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Store in refrigerator.
Makes at least one quart.
Let set for several hours or it will be soupy.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Peel the peaches; remove seed.
Mash to a pulp.
Squeeze juice from orange; add to peach pulp.
Put orange rind through food chopper.
Add to peach pulp.
Measure this pulp and add an equal amount of sugar.
Cook slowly until the desired thickness is reached.
Be sure to stir often to prevent scorching.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mash graham crackers very fine. Melt butter and mix with sugar and graham cracker crumbs. Press into dish.

title: pudding delight
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, butter, water and 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; pick off bones and cut to bite-size pieces. Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Mix in stuffing to moisten.
In a bowl blend soup, sour cream, mushrooms, parsley, salt and pepper; add chicken.
Spread mixture over the layer of stuffing.
Top with Ritz crackers which have been finely crumbled. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place in a shallow pan.
Place onions in skillet and cook until soft.
Add water, vinegar, sugar, salt, chili sauce, mustard and Tabasco sauce; mix well.
Pour sauce over chops and bake, covered, in a 350° oven, about 1 hour. Yields 4 servings.

title: stir-n-roll biscuits
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour oil and milk into measuring cup but do not stir.
Pour all at once into flour mixture.
Stir with fork until mixture leaves side of bowl. Roll and cut.
Place on greased pan.
Bake at 475° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
8 or 9 large biscuits.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco until sugar dissolves.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately to first mixture.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add any type of fruit topping to cake when serving (optional).

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain mixed fruit and cherries.
Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Slowly stir vanilla pudding and almond extract into pineapple juice until thickened.
Add mixed fruit, pineapple chunks and cherries.
Chill.

title: crab chantilly
directions: Cook green onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and cayenne pepper.
Add milk.
Stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Ranch dressing, catsup and crab.
Heat, but do not cook.
Spoon warm crab over cooked asparagus.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes (until lightly browned).
Serve over toast.
(An attractive and easy dish for company.)

title: strawberry-lemonade punch
directions: Make lemonade according to directions.
Add the slightly defrosted strawberries and the ginger ale.
Pour over ice to serve. (This recipe will make 24 servings.
For 500 servings, use 20 of each ingredient; for 100, use 40 of each.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place all ingredients into microwave container.
Heat until melted.
Blend well and pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: In large skillet over medium heat saute onion and garlic in the Butter buds.
Add chicken broth and tomatoes.
Add spaghetti, break up tomatoes if they are whole.
Add picante sauce and cumin, cover and simmer until spaghetti is cooked.
Add chicken.
Put in sprayed (no fat) casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: pecan carrot bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in coconut, pecans and raisins.
Blend in carrots, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into oiled and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes before removing.

title: caramels
directions: Put
sugar,
Karo
syrup,
cup
cream
and butter in saucepan. Heat over medium heat until it boils; stir constantly. After
it boils, add remaining cup of cream and boil until soft ball stage, stirring occasionally (sticks easily).	Pour in a buttered
square
pan
with
cup nuts in the bottom (optional).
Put
in
refrigerator, cut in squares and wrap in wax paper.

title: dixie potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin
on.
When cool, skin and dice. Dice eggs, celery and
onion.
Mix
sour
cream and mayonnaise together, then add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: green chile eggs
directions: Place shredded cheddar cheese in bottom of 13 X 9 inch glass baking dish.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix cocoa and food color to make a paste.
Add to sugar and egg mixture.
Sift flour and salt; add alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Mix vinegar and soda; blend gently.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; cool before frosting.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Layer thawed broccoli, chicken, soup and mayonnaise.
Mix together.
Place water chestnuts and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
During the last 5 minutes of cooking, sprinkle 1 can of fried onions on top.

title: pizza roll
directions: Brown sausage with a little onion and green pepper.
Mix hot roll mix according to package directions.
Cover and let rise in warm place while you slice pepperoni and grate cheese.
Roll out dough on floured surface about as large as a cookie sheet.
Spread sausage. Cut pepperoni and cheese almost to the ends.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Secure ends and place seam side down on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20-25
minutes.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with chipped beef.
Lay chicken on beef.
Mix cream or milk with soup and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 2 hours.
About 5 minutes before done, uncover and sprinkle with paprika.
Put back in oven for last 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening and sugar and beat in eggs one at a time.
Gradually add molasses, beating constantly.
Blend in dry ingredients using low speed on mixer.
Add water.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into well-greased and floured 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oven barbecue sauce
directions: In a 2-cup measuring cup, fill to 1 cup mark with ketchup.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Fill to 2 cup line with water and mix.
Pour over chicken parts in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked cheese potatoes
directions: Spread sliced potatoes in bottom of an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add onion, pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour cheddar cheese soup, diluted with milk, over the top of potatoes. Bake for 1 hour or until done in a slow oven.

title: pecan pie perfect no run
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in pie crust.
Set in iron skillet.
Bake at 350° until center is firm.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake, water, frozen strawberries, flour, oil, eggs and gelatin well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or 3 layer pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Soften butter or oleo and place in blender with milk, sugar, baking mix, eggs and vanilla.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until pie is set and top is golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: beef mushroom stew
directions: Place flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add beef cubes and shake to coat on all sides.
Brown beef in oil in large saucepan.
Stir in broth, water, mushrooms, onion, bay leaves, garlic and parsley; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Thicken, if desired. Serve over rice or noodles.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fried fruit pies
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening together until mealy.
Beat egg; add water and vinegar.
Add to dry mixture; mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Pinch off a small amount of dough and roll thin.
Use large saucer to cut dough around.
Place fruit (well drained) on 1/2 dough; put small amount of margarine on fruit, then pinch of cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon sugar.
Fold over other half dough, pressing edges together to seal (with fork). Fry in oil until brown on both sides.
When cool, dribble glaze on top or roll in powdered sugar.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake in slow oven at
325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamed crab and spinach soup
directions: Drain and slice crab, reserving liquid.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain and chop coarsely.
Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan.
Add celery and onion and saute until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling.
Add cream and reserved crab liquid.
Stir in crab and spinach.
Cook until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Put in glass pan.
Pour 1/2 can of tomato sauce over top of meat loaf.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean dip
directions: Cook in pan over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: skillet shepherd's pie
directions: In a large skillet, combine all of the ingredients, except the potatoes. Mix well and cook over high heat about 5 to 6 minutes until heated through, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and dollop with potatoes. Serve immediately.

title: 14 carrot cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix sugar, eggs, oil, pineapple, nuts and carrots in a medium bowl.
Combine in large bowl with sifted ingredients and stir until blended. Bake in 3 layers or sheet pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake completely and frost.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and oleo.
Combine flour and baking soda and add to creamed mixture.
Add salt, vinegar and vanilla.
Drop mixture by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(They spread out.)

title: glazed snow peas and carrots
directions: In cup mix cornstarch and 1 cup broth until smooth. Set aside.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel thin strip around center of apple.
Core apple to within 1 to 2 inches of bottom.
Fill with above ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in microwave 2 to 3 minutes per apple.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add unbeaten eggs. Sift in all dry ingredients. Add vanilla, coconut, pecans and figs. Beat well. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine in a bowl Rice Krispies and nut meats.
In a pan cut dates and add sugar, egg and oleo.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix all together.
Butter hands and roll in rolls or balls, then roll in coconut.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and add water.
Heat to boiling, then simmer for 50 minutes.
Add onions the last 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour meat in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange potatoes on top of meat.
Stir soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over meat and potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cereal.
Bake 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Precook squash in water 10 minutes.
Mash squash and mix other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all above ingredients together.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook corn and drain.
Layer in casserole dish:
1/2 corn, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 milk, dash of salt and pepper, sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with margarine; then repeat layers.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cracker crumbs are browned.

title: salmon cheese pie
directions: Open the salmon and flake. Save juice. Mix and spread in pie shell. Cover top with American cheese slices. Place pie crust on top. Cut slits in top and bake until brown.

title: easy split pea soup(microwave)
directions: In 2 quart casserole, combine carrots, onions, potatoes and water.
Cover.
Microwave at
High
for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add
soup, milk, ham and seasonings to vegetables.
Microwave at High
for 5 to 10 minutes or until soup is thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate. (Wrap in Saran Wrap first.)
Will keep for several weeks.
May roll in ground pecans before refrigeration.

title: citrus pork chops
directions: Cut the scallions into 2-inch lengths.
Using a sharp knife, cut thin strips of zest (about 1/2-inch wide) from 1 orange and 1 lemon.
Space the strips about 1/2-inch apart to create a striped effect.
Cut the orange and lemon crosswise into thin slices. Grate the zest from the remaining orange and lemon, then juice the orange and measure out 1/4 cup of juice.
Juice the lemon to get about 1/4 cup of juice.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients until smooth, then add egg and beat.
Pour into a 10-inch pie shell; sprinkle with pecans and set aside.
Beat gently the eggs, sugar, vanilla and Karo.
Pour into pie shell over previous ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set cream cheese and Cheddar cheese out for 2 hours.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs and beat again.
Spread an 8 1/2 x 12-inch pan with all but 3 tablespoons of crushed graham crackers.
Spread mixture on top of crackers. Cover with pineapple.
Whip cream; spread on top of pineapple. Mix reserved graham crackers and walnuts; sprinkle over cake. Freeze 3 to 4 hours.
Thaw slightly to serve.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together and let stand until dough doubles in size.
Make out into desired shape.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: orange dill braised chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In a pressure cooker, over high heat, brown the chicken on all sides in olive oil, in several batches.
Remove chicken.
Add the orange zest, garlic, dill and wine.
Stir to remove any brown bits clinging to the bottom of the pan.
Bring to a boil and add chicken broth and reserved brown chicken pieces.
Seal pressure cooker and cook over high heat until steam flows steadily.
Turn heat down so that steam keeps a constant stream.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat, cool pressure cooker under running cold water and release steam.
Open cooker carefully; add carrots, celery and pepper. Seal cooker and cook for 2 minutes.
Release steam and open cooker.
Remove chicken and vegetables to a deep dish.
Dissolve cornstarch in the orange juice and add to the liquid in the pan. Boil until lightly thickened, about 1 minute.
Pour over chicken and serve.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine everything except vanilla.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a soft ball (238° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: low calorie chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil. Pour over excess oil.
Add water, contents of gravy mix and paprika. Cover and simmer 40 to 50 minutes until tender. Remove from heat and stir in buttermilk. Heat, but do not boil.

title: fudgy chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Add eggs, stirring well to mix.
Do not beat.
Add vanilla and milk; mix.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue cooking for 25 minutes or until filling is set.

title: fancy pea casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in melted margarine until tender. Add mushroom soup, chopped pimento and water chestnuts.
Pour this mixture over peas (drained).
Bake in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.

title: one-dish meal casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add cheese soup and water, stirring well.
Add tomatoes, mustard and corn.
Stir in noodles.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly with vinegar, then add sugar and meal. Melt butter; add it and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done.

title: calico bean soup
directions: Place mixture of dried beans in a large kettle.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain and add 2 quarts fresh water and ham bone or hock.
Simmer slowly for 2 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer another 45 minutes, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: baked stew(i call this "fake" sirloin tips)
directions: Bake, uncovered, 3 1/2 hours at 300°.
May thicken with a little flour, if needed, before serving over a bed of rice or noodles.
Freezes well.

title: blueberry buckle(great with coffee in the morning!!)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg and beat.
Mix dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk, having dry ingredients first and last. Spread batter in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with blueberries.

title: homecoming cornmeal bread
directions: Heat black cast-iron frypan (spider) while mixing batter. Beat ingredients until smooth.
Grease pan or use oil.
Serve topped with warm applesauce, syrup or butter and sugar.
These pancakes raise nicely while "baking" atop the stove.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Boil macaroni; grate cheese and put a small amount aside.
In a large bowl, put hot macaroni, cheese, butter, milk and eggs; mix well until the cheese is melted.
Put into a casserole dish, garnish with small amount of cheese; set aside.
Bake at 350° until top cheese is melted.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, water and salt.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix together grated cheese, onion, celery and mayonnaise and pour mixture over the vegetable mixture.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.
Can be halved for smaller group.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Cream together sugar, brown sugar, shortening and peanut butter. Add egg. Add dry ingredients. Mix until no flour is showing. Make into balls the size of a quarter. Flatten with a fork dipped in flour, making a crisscross design. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° until set but not brown.

title: walnut sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a large mixer bowl, heat hot yams with butter until smooth. Add remaining ingredients, setting aside pastry shell. Bake 30 minutes. Remove pie from oven; spoon Walnut Topping evenly over top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until pie is golden brown. Cool. Serve warm or chilled. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mom's italian beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together in Dutch oven; cover and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes.
Spoon on hard rolls and serve. Better the second time around; just heat and eat.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine peas, onion and green pepper in medium bowl.
Add garlic and vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Add to vegetable mixture and toss lightly to coat.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: german potato salad dressing
directions: Combine water, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Chop bacon and brown.
Skim out bacon and put into water mixture.
Fry onions in bacon fat until soft.
Add flour.
Let bubble up to 2 to 3 minutes.
Add this roux to hot water mixture. Stir until smooth.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix into boiled or canned sliced potatoes.

title: no-stir, lo-cal skillet casserole
directions: Saute ground turkey in skillet.
I add water because turkey meat is very dry.
Add tomatoes (save small amount for over top of noodles).
Add noodles and then rest of tomatoes over top.
(Do not stir.)
Cover; simmer until noodles are soft, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Make sure it does not get dry.
(Add water.)
When noodles are cooked; add slices of cheese over top.
Cover until cheese melts and serve from skillet.
An easy, quick meal. Go-o-o-o-d.

title: granny's corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs in a bowl.
Add both cans of corn, sugar and cornstarch.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make sure center is firm.

title: iced tea
directions: Fill
medium pan with water.
Bring to a boil.
Add tea bags and
remove
from heat.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove tea
bags and pour in sugar, stirring until dissolved. Pour
into a 2-quart pitcher and finish filling with cold tap water.
Stir.

title: hot mexican bean dip
directions: Sieve pork and beans.
Combine all ingredients except bacon in saucepan.
Heat through.
Top with bacon.

title: clam dip
directions: Melt butter. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: aunt zeta's vegetable soup
directions: Cook the meat and the potatoes (not together) however, you may cook the onion with the potatoes or fry with the hamburger, whichever you prefer.
Cook all together and simmer until you are ready to eat.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Melt margarine in skillet, partially drain sauerkraut and add to skillet; sprinkle with rice and onion.
Top with crumbled ground beef.
Spread salt, pepper and tomato sauce evenly on top to cover hamburger.
Cover skillet, cook over low heat 25 to 30 minutes. You may use sausage as a substitute and adjust added salt.
Layer each section to cover skillet bottom.

title: crab cocktail cracker dip
directions: Mix all.
Pour over brick of cream cheese. Spread on crackers.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Refrigerate. Mix occasionally.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Warm bowl, then mix 3 tablespoons sugar and yeast and stir. Add egg, vanilla and butter to liquid, then add hot roll mix. Flour table and knead dough.
Put back in oiled bowl.
Cover and let rise double in size, then cut in 3 equal parts.
Roll one part on cookie sheet.
Spread butter on it and sprinkle on cinnamon, sugar, nuts and raisins, then roll out the next two parts following same steps, putting them on top of each other and forming 3 layers.
Put a glass in middle of dough, cut through at least 2 layers of the dough, then take knife and cut from glass out (like cutting pizza).
Make 16 cuts.
Pick up each cut, twist it and lay back where you picked it up from.
Let rise again, then bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Add together biscuit mix, sausage and cheese. Form into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: huckleberry and peach strudel
directions: Make pastry with flour, butter, cold water and egg yolk. Chill 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll dough to 12 x 16-inch rectangle. Trim to 10 x 15-inches, reserving trimmings.
Transfer to large baking sheet. Brush 5 x 8-inches in center with half of the melted butter.
Sprinkle combination of almonds, coconut and wafer crumbs over buttered area.
Mix fruit, sugar, peel and lemon juice.
Spread over crumbs. Arrange reserved strips over filling in lattice pattern.
Fold long sides of pastry, then short ends. Brush with remaining melted butter. Bake 25 minutes. Transfer to serving platter. Cool 15 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Season to taste.
Place in layers sliced raw potatoes about 1-inch thick in bottom of large casserole bowl.
Combine tomato soup, 1/2 soup can milk, chopped celery, chopped green pepper and uncooked Minute rice.
Pour half of mixture over potato slices.
Layer half of hamburger mixture, tomato mixture and remaining hamburger.
Top with thin layer of potato slices.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
Just as good the second day.

title: wacky water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon in half.
Wrap chestnuts in bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes until crisp.
Drain fat.
Bring remaining ingredients to a rolling boil.
Spoon sauce over chestnuts.
May refrigerate at this point.
When ready to serve, bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and run cold water over until cool.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and pat into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until nice and brown.
Serve hot.
These freeze well.
Can be put back on a tray, warmed and then served.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix together and heat thoroughly. Serve hot. Serves approximately 100.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together; pour over chicken. Crush crackers; mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, until brown.

title: walnut florentines
directions: Combine butter, cream and brown sugar in saucepan; heat slowly until butter melts.
Remove from heat, stir in flour and salt and blend until smooth.
Stir in walnuts and orange peel.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten lightly with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 1 or 2 minutes on cookie sheet then remove with spatula to wire rack to cool.
When cool, melt chocolate and spread bottoms of cookies with thin layer of chocolate.

title: sauteed fresh tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick.
Dredge in seasoned flour. Saute in margarine until golden brown on both sides.
Just before serving, sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: squash pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in medium bowl with mixer.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together, then form into balls and bake until lightly browned. Let cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: fudge-walnut brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs in large bowl, stir in sugar, oleo and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until set. Cool.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh tomato toss
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Toss hot spaghetti with butter, tomatoes, green onion, basil, salt, pepper and cheese.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Open can of oysters; drain liquid into a measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup, then add enough milk to make 2 1/2 cups of liquid.
Crumble 11 crackers into buttered baking dish.
Place drained oysters on top of crackers.
If onions are used, sprinkle on top of oysters.
Dot with the margarine.
Beat the eggs; add to 2 1/2 cups of liquid.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Crumble the other 11 crackers over oyster mixture.
Pour milk and egg mixture over crackers.
Store in refrigerator overnight, or until the milk mixture has puffed up the crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven until puffed up and brown.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl, tossing to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Makes 8 servings.

title: creole carrots
directions: Place carrots and salt in saucepan containing about 1 inch boiling water.
Simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add hot water to liquid to make 1 cup. Dissolve bouillon in carrot liquid and set aside.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple together; add sour cream, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix until blended.
Pour into a container.

title: esther's pie crust
directions: Mix flour
and salt in bowl;
cut in shortening to size of peas.
Sprinkle with water and stir with a fork.

title: broccoli burger bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni in 6 cups salted water (4 teaspoons salt) 8 minutes and drain.
Cook and stir ground beef until light brown and drain.
Mix beef, macaroni, sauce mix, broccoli, water, walnuts, parsley, salt and garlic powder in ungreased, 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with croutons.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop 1/2 cup of popcorn and put into a grocery sack.
Boil oleo, syrup and sugar for 2 minutes.
Be sure this boils.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda to this when it is done and stir until foamy.
Pour over popcorn in sack.
Close and shake.
Put in microwave with top of sack open for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out, shake and repeat 2 more times.
When finished, spread out on table and tap on popcorn to separate until dry.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling water to cover with 1/2 teaspoon salt for 5 minutes, drain. In a large bowl, stir together 1/2 teaspoon salt, butter, crackers, sugar and pepper, mix well. Stir in cauliflower, bell pepper, tomatoes, onion and 1 1/4 cups cheese. Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Serve immediately.

title: lemon sauce for cakes
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in water. Stir in egg; cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Do not boil.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon rind and juice.

title: raisin-rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole. Place casserole in pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Add broccoli for last 4 minutes of cooking time, then drain. Heat butter in large skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned, stirring often. Add soup, milk, cheese, pepper and spaghetti mixture and heat through. Serve with additional Parmesan cheese.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: never fail frosting
directions: Let water reach boiling in bottom of double boiler.
Combine sugar, salt, cream of tartar, eggs, and water in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water.
Use high speed on mixer and beat until frosting is fluffy and holds its shape (about 7-8 minutes).
Add vanilla and spread on cake.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix and spread 1 heaping tablespoonful on each tortilla. Starting at one end, roll up each tortilla tightly.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Serve with picante sauce or salsa for dipping.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted boiling water until almost tender. Drain.
Simmer onion in margarine; add flour, salt and mustard. Add milk and cook until smooth.
Add pepper and celery salt.

title: lemon thin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until edges are golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Great tea cookie!

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Heat milk.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Beat egg whites.
Combine; cook 30 minutes at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook green peppers and onions; add hamburg and cook well.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 3 or 4 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and chill several hours or overnight.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Make a roux with the oil and flour, stirring constantly until tan, add salt and pepper to taste. Lower heat and add tomato juice slowly, this will sizzle. Keep stirring until thickened. If gravy becomes too thick for your taste, thin with water.

title: cali's culinary cuisine
directions: Put bread in toaster.
Spread butter on bread when it pops up. Enjoy.

title: bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease Bundt pan generously (even the nonstick ones).
Combine sugar, flour, margarine, eggs and flavorings in an electric mixer all at once and beat until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake one hour or until cake is done.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Parboil unpeeled sweet potatoes.
Peel and cut in half. Arrange in a cook-and-serve
baking dish.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix sugar with oranges. Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: frank and pineapple kabobs
directions: Cut franks in 1-inch lengths.
Put on skewers alternately with drained pineapple chunks.
Mix together the mustard and the pineapple syrup.
Brush on the skewered franks and pineapple. Broil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Turn over.
Boil for another 3 minutes. Brush mixture on skewered franks after turned over.
Serve hot.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and cut other ingredients fine.
Combine ingredients in bowl and pour the mixture of vinegar, sugar and oil over.
Stir well.
Let stand in refrigerator a few hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Boil noodles and drain.
Mix sauce and hamburger together.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 layer of noodles.
Put sauce and hamburger over noodles.
Add half of container of cottage cheese and cover with 2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Add another layer of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix everything and add hash brown potatoes-reserve enough cheese to sprinkle on top.
Place in long casserole dish and bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: hershey 5 layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, melt butter or margarine in oven.
Combine crumbs, cocoa and sugar; sprinkle over butter or margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, then raisins, apricots or marshmallows.
Sprinkle nuts on top; press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; cover with foil.
Allow to set at room temperature about 8 hours before cutting into bars.
Makes about 36 bars.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix all dry ingredients together.
In small bowl, mix all liquids and combine mixtures.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
If using a glass pan, lower to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Makes one large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove crusts from bread and cube. Line bottom of pan with cubes.
Cook sausage and drain.
Sprinkle over bread.
Cover with cheeses and mushrooms.
Combine cream, milk and eggs.
Add seasonings and pour over other ingredients. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: ambrosia
directions: Fold ingredients together.
Make sure the fruit is drained well.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese and dressing mix until well mixed. Add drained chicken and blend well. Form a ball and roll into chopped nuts, some poppy seeds or sesame seeds and a little dill weed. Serve with crackers. Better next day.

title: pickled squash
directions: Add
squash, onions, pepper and pimento to a large pot, then add salt and water and soak for 1 hour.
Drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar,
mustard and celery seed and bring to a boil. Add vegetables
and
bring to a boil again.
Pour hot mixture into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on
bands.
Process
in
hot water bath for 10 minutes. Yield: 4 quarts.

title: spinach balls(bet you can't eat just one!)
directions: Mix croutons, eggs, Parmesan cheese and paprika into spinach. Shape into balls about the size of walnuts.
Freeze on cookie sheets.

title: chocolate sheet cake(also known as texas sheet cake)
directions: Combine sugar and flour together in large bowl.
Combine margarine and cocoa and water together in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon cinnamon (optional), 1 teaspoon soda, 1 teaspoon vanilla and pinch of salt.
Mix and pour into 16 x 11-inch jelly roll pan (greased and lightly floured).

title: delicious rhubarb pie
directions: Combine and mix well the egg, sugar, flour and salt.
Arrange rhubarb in unbaked pie shell, spread egg mixture over rhubarb. Pat down.
Then top crust.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients well and enjoy with chips!

title: katie's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Check with tester.
If comes out wet or moist, turn oven to 400° and bake 5 more minutes.
How to cook your pumpkin?
After cutting pumpkin up, place in large pot with 1 cup water.
Cook on medium heat until tender.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Whip butter and peanut butter until smooth.
Add sugar and cream together.
Add egg and mix.
Blend dry ingredients, then add to butter mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crab muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine crab, cheese spread, butter, mayonnaise, garlic powder and salt.
Spread over muffins.
Broil 4 to 6-inches from heat for 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut each muffin into quarters.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Good on carrot cake.

title: apple-blueberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put apples and blueberries in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour water over top.
Combine cake mix, brown sugar, melted butter and spices.
Stir until well blended. (Mixture will be crumbly.) Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Saute the bacon until crisp and then crumble it.
Mix remaining ingredients with the bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade chili beans
directions: Season ground meat. Brown together ground meat, onion, celery and garlic. Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Add tomato sauce and water. Stir.
Add the kidney beans. Mix well. Rinse cans with a little water.
Pour in pot.
Simmer about 30 minutes or more.

title: 2 egg cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Put shortening in large mixing bowl and cream until softened.
Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Beat.
Add eggs and beat after each.
Pour batter into 2 greased cake pans or 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes for layers, or 35 minutes for loaf cake.

title: pecan roll
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients together slowly until it forms a solid ball in cold water.
Add the dates and pecans.
Spoon onto well floured (or powdered sugar) surface; shape in long roll shape. Store in refrigerator.

title: hazel fryback's lemon cake pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks, flour, lemon juice and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Fold in 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Test by inserting knife blade into center.
It should come out clean.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In saucepan, combine chocolate chips, Eagle Brand and oleo. Heat over low heat until chocolate is melted; remove from heat. In large bowl, combine marshmallows and peanuts.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan whose sides and bottom have been lined with wax paper.
Chill 2 hours, or until firm. Remove from pan; peel off wax paper.
Cut into 1-inch squares with wet knife.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Add eggs, 1 at time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Chill.
Top with fruit.

title: vinegar cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar and vinegar.
Add flour, baking soda and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: roasted potatoes with garlic
directions: In a large baking pan, toss potatoes with garlic, oil, salt and pepper.
Roast in a preheated 500° oven, stirring once for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in small amount of butter.
Combine other ingredients, except cheese.
Add onion.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 1 hour.
Garnish with cheese the last 15 minutes.

title: succulent barbecue sauce
directions: Steam onions, celery and green pepper until tender or microwave on High for 3 minutes or until tender.
Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Serve over chicken, ribs, pork chops, smoked sausage, etc.

title: garlic-parmesan potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 9 x 1 1/2-inch quiche dish with nonstick spray.
Mix mashed potatoes, sour cream, 1/3 cup cheese and garlic in quiche dish; spread evenly.
Arrange potato wedges in spoke fashion with 2 wedges in center of mixture.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chives.

title: red cabbage
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and cabbage; stir.
Fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Add boiling water as needed (not much).
Add apple pieces; stir.
Add pepper, bay leaf and cloves and stir.
Add boiling water, about 1 cup.
Stir, cover and simmer about 1/2 hour.
Check for water often.
Stir repeatedly.
Add sugar and vinegar; stir.
Taste for sour-sweetness.
(Leftover red cabbage reheated tastes extra good!)

title: poppy seed cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.

title: macaroni, cheese and tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to box directions.
Drain.
Add tuna (drained), mixed vegetables (drained) and cream of celery soup. Stir all together.
Add about 1/2 of the Longhorn cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with crumbled crackers and slice the rest of the cheese over top of crackers.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Put in microwave or oven until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: best chocolate cake with fudge frosting
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 3 rounded 8 x 1 1/2-inch pans or 2 rounded 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Beat all ingredients except fudge frosting in large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly. Beat on high speed for 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Pour into pans.
Bake rectangular pan for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Round pans should be baked 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meringue topping
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Meringue should be very stiff, but not dry.
Spoon evenly over top of filling of a 9-inch pie in an ovenproof glass or ceramic pie dish.
Attach to edge of crust so meringue will not shrink during cooking.
Do not spread too smooth.
Place pie on tray shelf in center position.
Cook with microwave at Medium (50%) for 3 to 4 minutes or until meringue is set.
Brown 4 to 5 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: colorful corn salad
directions: Best when prepared a day ahead!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix
ingredients
together
thoroughly and bake in loaf pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: crustless meat pie
directions: Combine ingredients in baking dish.
Top with Stove Top stuffing mix with seasoning.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.
Serve.

title: quick popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn in popper and place in bowl.
Mix together sugar, salt, coloring and syrup.
Pour over the popped corn and shape into ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss together, refrigerate overnight.
(Can be served after it chills for an hour or so also.)

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prepare Potato Cream Cheese Filling first.
(Note: Filling can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated overnight in a covered container.)

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cook carrots in 1 1/2 cups of water until tender.
Drain 2/3 of liquid from
carrots.
When done; set aside.
In saucepan, peel orange after scraping 1 tablespoon of peeling into saucepan and cut up over saucepan to save any juice.
Add finely cut up onions. Heat until almost boiling.
Combine carrots and honey.
If orange is not real sweet, add a little more honey.
Excellent change for ho-hum carrots.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add pepperoni to beef to warm. In casserole dish layer meat, spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Warm in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple snowballs
directions: Beat cream cheese with wooden spoon until soft. Gradually beat in confectioners sugar, salt, pineapple and mini marshmallows. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in vanilla wafers. Chill.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: potato salad
directions: Chop potatoes into cube size pieces.
Add mayonnaise and mustard; mix with potatoes.
(May need to add more to make creamy.)
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken
directions: Melt the margarine in a frying pan. Saute the chicken in the margarine. Add a little salt and pepper. Place the cooked chicken in a baking dish and add the mushrooms and onions. Let bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: old-fashioned dark chocolate cake
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Add sour milk alternately with combined flour, salt and soda.
Stir cocoa into water until dissolved.
Add to batter and mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared pans (use either 9 or 10-inch tube or three 8-inch layers).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes for tube or 35 to 40 minutes for layer pans.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix pecans, coconut, brown sugar and flour.
Stir in 2 tablespoons melted butter and sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: magnificent mostaccioli
directions: Boil brats; remove skins and cut up.
Add everything else except noodles and cheese; simmer at least 1 hour.
Cook mostaccioli according to package directions.
Drain and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover noodles with sauce and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until warmed through.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in microwave, then add sugar and Pet milk. Cook on medium heat and stir until rolling boil forms. Boil for 5 minutes and take off burner. Add vanilla, Marshmallow Crme, peanut butter chips and peanut butter. Use only Jif. Pour in pan and refrigerate.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
In large saucepan, combine water, broths, undrained tomatoes, onion and green pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add corn, chili powder, cumin and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes more.
To serve, place crushed chips into each bowl. Ladle soup over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese, avocado and cilantro.
Serve with lime wedge.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed hot dogs
directions: Mash potatoes; add salad dressing, relish and eggs.
Mix lightly.
Season to taste.
Fill hot dogs with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: catsup
directions: Simmer for 3 to 4 hours in a large kettle.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and cover to seal.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with refried beans.
Spread the avocado on top.
Spread the sour cream on top of the avocado layer.
Spread the tomatoes over the sour cream.
Sprinkle the black olives over the tomatoes followed by the green onions. Cover the top with the cheddar cheese.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: country herb bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the yeast and sugar in warm water. Let stand until foamy, 5 to 10 minutes.
In small saucepan, heat the herbs with the milk until lukewarm.

title: arroz con pollo(rice with chicken)
directions: To a pot of boiling water, add the cleaned pieces of chicken and cook for about 1 hour on medium heat.
Save 3 cups of that broth with the chicken.
Saute diced green pepper, onion, garlic, olives and capers.
Add tomato sauce, salt and oregano and saute some more.
Then add the broth.
Bring to a boil.
Then add the rice.
Bring to a boil again; lower the heat to simmer.
Cover. Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn once.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together in a pan sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Cook over medium heat until it starts to boil, stirring occasionally. Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool for 1 minute, then add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal, stirring well.
Drop spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: cheesecake mousse
directions: Place milk in a deep bowl with beaters.
Freeze until ice crystals start to form.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and cool to room temperature.
Beat icy milk on high until light and fluffy.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl until fluffy. Blend in cooled gelatin and vanilla.
Add whipped evaporated milk.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into dessert glasses and sprinkle with crumbs.
Chill 3 hours.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco, salt and flour; add beaten egg, water and vinegar. Place on a floured board and work some.
Makes 3 pie crusts or if you want to freeze this and make pie crusts later, form into 3 large balls, unthaw later and roll out on a floured board.

title: quick barbecue mix
directions: Put ground beef and chopped onion in pan and fry over moderate heat until done.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper and add to beef mixture, stirring well.
Add catsup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well.
Heat and serve on hot buns.

title: vegetable, shrimp and pasta
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat margarine or butter over medium high heat and cook shrimp and garlic; stirring frequently, 2 minutes or until shrimp turn almost pink.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine, salt and pecans.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
