title: saucy pizza rolls
directions: Cook lasagne noodles to desired doneness as directed on package.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Heat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, brown ground beef with onion; drain.

Stir in 1/4 cup of the pizza sauce, 1/2 cup of the cheese, mushrooms and egg. Spread each lasagne noodle with a generous 1/3 cup meat mixture; carefully roll up and place seam side down in ungreased 8-inch (2-quart) square baking dish.
Pour remaining pizza sauce over rolls.
Cover; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake an additional 4 to 6 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: tuna tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into pieces and cook following package directions.
Drain; mix soup, 1/4 of liquid from mushrooms, drained mushrooms, chopped onion, pimento, green pepper and 1 1/4 cups of the cheese.
Add spaghetti, tuna (broken into chunks) and sherry; toss lightly until mixed.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Put into casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake in moderate oven, 350°, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water (warm). Add oil and salt. Put flour in mixing bowl. Pour in yeast mixture. Mix and knead. Roll out. Put in greased pan. Let rise 45 minutes. Bake at 475° until done.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake mix following directions on box. Save 1 cup of cake batter. Grease 9 x 13 baking pan. Pour cake mix into pan and bake at 350°.

title: cheesy sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage with onion and drain off grease.
Mix together with other ingredients and cook until cheese is melted.
Can be placed in slow cooker until cheese has melted.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat sour cream, cream cheese, onion dip, taco seasoning and salt together for 10 minutes.
Spread on a flat type serving plate and refrigerate at least 1 hour to firm mixture.
Sprinkle chopped lettuce, tomatoes and shredded Cheddar over dip.
Serve with taco chips for dipping.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Add chili and Tabasco. Heat 2 minutes on High.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Heat 1 minute. Serve with chips (Tostitos)

title: pat's pasta
directions: Combine vegetables, olives and cheese. Blend in enough Hellmann's mayonnaise to moisten and hold together well.
Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse in cold water and drain well. Fold other ingredients into pasta and check for correct amount of mayonnaise. Add salt and pepper.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Cut onions and pepper into slices and mix with cooled carrots.
Mix other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours or more. Drain to serve (or keep and return unused vegetables).
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn & sausage chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, brown sausage and drain. In 2 tbsp. drippings saute onion & sausage. Add next 5 ingredients. Cover and cook until potatoes are done. Stir in corn & milk and heat to almost boiling. Serves 6 - 8.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together cream, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into freezer canister, then fill to the top with milk.
Freeze.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Mix confectionary sugar, vanilla, and milk.
Stir until hard. Flour wax paper- Lay
mixture on wax paper roll it out flat and thin, spread peanut butter.
Start at one side, roll into log. Take sharp knife, cut into slices.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 9 1/2-inch Bundt pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Combine 6 tablespoons Kahlua and powdered sugar.
When cake is warm in pan, poke holes in cake and pour glaze over. Allow cake to cool in pan at least 2 hours before removing.
Good with whipped cream.

title: brazilian coconut cookies
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar and water and cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook until syrup reaches a temperature of 230° on a candy thermometer.
In a small bowl, mix egg yolks and flour together, blend well.
Add 2 tablespoons of syrup, stirring.
Slowly pour mixture into syrup in the saucepan, stirring constantly.
Add coconut and simmer over low heat, stirring, until mixture is thick and stiff.
Don't allow mixture to come to a boil.
Remove the pan from the heat, stir in the vanilla and let cool to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape mixture into small balls, 1 tablespoonful at a time. Butter cookie sheet and bake cookies in oven for 15 minutes.
Cool. Makes 40 cookies.

title: cranberry layer cake
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in a large bowl. Mix well and stir in cranberrys and walnuts. Pour in two greased 9 inch round baking pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans. Cool completely.

title: quickie chocolate drink
directions: Blend all together and serve chilled.
Heat in top of double boiler over simmering water for a hot drink.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add sugar to cranberries and let set overnight.
Add crushed pineapple, nuts, marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: marinated poppy seed vegetable salad
directions: In blender or food processor, mix the first 5 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables, cover, and put in refrigerator for at least 24 hours. 48 hours is recommended.
You can add pimento or chopped red pepper for color when serving if you like.
(If you add to mixture before day of serving it will make the sauce pink.)

title: el dorado casserole
directions: Cook meat; drain.
Add olives, onion and tomato sauce.
Mix sour cream, cottage cheese and Ortegas.
In a 14 x 9-inch baking dish, crumble 1/2 the tortilla chips, lining the bottom of the pan.
Next, spread 1/2 the meat mixture over chips, then 1/2 the sour cream mixture over top.
Layer again, starting with chips, then meat, then sour cream mixture.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 5.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across the grain into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Stir and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Add beef and stir over high heat until brown.
Taste; if not tender, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables. Stir until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water; add to pan, stirring and cooking until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve over cooked white or brown rice.

title: "no-fat" chicken tortillas
directions: Marinate chicken with Gavenders seasonings to taste and red pepper.
Grill 10 minutes on each side until done.
Slice chicken in strips or cubes.
Warm tortillas.

title: holiday poke cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package for two 9-inch round cake layers.
Cool.
Place cake layers, top side up, in 2 clean round cake pans.
Pierce cake with large fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Stir one cup boiling water into each flavor of gelatin in separate bowls for 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Pour one flavor of gelatin over one layer and the other flavor over the remaining layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Dip cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds and unmold onto serving plate.
Spread with 1/4 of the frosting.
Place second layer on top and do the same.
Refrigerate one hour before serving.

title: herbed cornish hens
directions: In a small bowl, combine salt, sage, allspice, pepper and rosemary.
Coat the hens with oil, then with the herb mixture, rubbing them well.
Cover the hens with plastic wrap and refrigerate 3 hours.
Preheat broiler.
Set rack 8 inches from heat.
Arrange hens on broiler pan and broil 8 minutes; turn over and broil 7 to 8 minutes longer.
Serves

title: hard candy
directions: Cook all together in large pan; use thermometer.
Use 260 coloring, 290 flavor, 300 lemon, sassafras, clover, anise, orange and cinnamon.
Pour in greased cookie sheet.
After cooled, break and cover with powdered sugar.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic together in large skillet; drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cheese. Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese and sprinkle over top of pineapple.
Mix crushed crackers with margarine and crumble over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add Spanish peanuts; stir.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes approximately 60 clusters.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pound into round steak.
Cut steak into small serving pieces.
Brown steak in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add French onion soup and ketchup.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add green pepper (cut into 8 strips).
Cook 20 minutes until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix sour cream, marshmallows, coconut and 1 can of cocktail, drained.
Add the other cocktail and both cans of oranges with juice.
Mix well. Cover and put in refrigerator for 24 hours and mix a few times during that time.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix well together the first 5 ingredients.
Then mix together the last 3 ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures and mix well. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Will keep in refrigerator (the batter) for six weeks.

title: burritos
directions: Cook and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
To burrito shell, fill meat, Monterey Jack cheese, beans, sour cream, black olives and salsa and roll.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with one cup crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter (or margarine).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be frozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix crackers, margarine, peanut butter and sugar.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips; top peanut butter mix.
Chill 10 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in lemon rind.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture along with raisins.
Mix well.
Drop teaspoonful on cookie sheet 2-inches apart and press flat.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 400° until light brown.
Remove cookies from pan while hot.

title: grandma rohde's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water.
Mix sugars, vanilla, eggs, salt, butter and dissolved soda.
Blend with mixture.
Add flour to mixture.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° until brown.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix and pour over cake immediately when removing from oven. Sprinkle coconut and/or pecans on top.

title: asparagus and new potatoes
directions: In a 12-inch skillet on high heat, bring 1 cup water to a boil; add potatoes with skin and carrots. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Drain vegetables and set aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Place sliced apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan. Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate as you would for dipping.
Stir in thoroughly but quickly the Eagle Brand milk.
If nuts are desired, put in chocolate before adding milk, as the fudge will begin to set up quickly.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Cook hamburger meat (and onion).
Add the remaining ingredients and cook until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: skillet chicken stew
directions: *Or sometimes I use chicken patties.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender. Blend soup and mayonnaise with 1/2 cup of cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place vegetables in a large pot with tomatoes and broth. Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, until thick, about 45 minutes.
Season with pepper.
Has zero fat.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Mix jello and hot water; let sit until partially jelled.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour in mold.
Refrigerate until jelled completely.
Perfect for Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix everything together and bake in single round buttered cake pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool on rack for 10 minutes and then take out carefully.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper and brown chops on both sides in skillet.
Arrange potatoes in 2-quart casserole. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Place brown chops on top of potatoes in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: popcorn snowmen
directions: In large pot over low heat, melt marshmallows and 3 tablespoons of butter or margarine, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are gooey.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the popped popcorn a little at a time.
Let the
pot cool for at least a minute.
Rub some butter or margarine on your hands.
Then, scoop out a handful of the mixture and make one ball for the body and one for the head.
Use decorations to make eyes, nose and mouth. If you make his body about the size of a tennis ball, this recipe makes about seven snowmen.

title: lightning microwave fudge
directions: Combine ingredients in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave on High for 2 or 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. When ready, the surface will become dull. Stir until smooth. Spread mixture into a buttered 8 x 8-inch glass dish. Cool and cut. Makes 8 to 10 servings. Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Mix 1 can of water into the cherries. Put into 9 x 13 glass dish. Sprinkle cake mix on top (dry). Slice butter thin and put on top of cake mix. Put into preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Layer bread, sausage and cheese into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt, dry mustard, 1 can mushroom soup and water.
Pour over casserole.
Let set overnight or 8 hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° (1 1/2 hours, covered, 1/2 hour uncovered) until center is done.
Test with knife.
Remove from oven and let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple butter
directions: Put the chopped apples in a crock pot. Sprinkle the sugar and cinnamon over the top. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour stirring occasionally. Add vinegar and stir. Reduce heat to low and continue cooking several hours until apples are consistency of apple sauce. Any large pieces of apples can be mashed with a potato masher or a fork. Continue cooking to thicken slightly. Spoon into jars and seal immediately.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, mashed bananas and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and chopped nuts.
Put in 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans and bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until a wooden pick comes out clean when inserted, at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pans.
Slice when cold.
Keeps moist when tightly wrapped. Freezes well.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and eggs until there is no sugar in the bottom of mixing bowl.
Gradually add eggs, one at a time; blend well.
Add all dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Add sour cream; mix at low speed.
Slowly add sweet milk until you get the texture you desire.
Add extract.
Increase speed to thoroughly blend all ingredients. Grease and flour a tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove tough outer leaves of cabbage. Core, then place it in a large kettle of boiling water.
Boil until outside leaves loosen. Lift out leaves with two wooden spoons and drain. In a bowl, combine meat, rice, onion, parsley, egg and salt, if desired.

Place about 2 tablespoons of the meat mixture in the center of each cabbage leaf, tuck in the sides over the meat and roll up securely. Place close together in a large, deep skillet. Add remaining ingredients and enough water to cover. Cover tightly and cook over medium heat 30 minutes, shaking pan occasionally. Serve or freeze for later use. To reheat, bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, until brown on top. Makes 24 rolls; allow 2 per serving.

title: pistachio
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
Add jello mix and stir.
Then add Cool Whip, marshmallows and crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: taco pie(makes 10)
directions: Flatten biscuit dough into pie shell shape in pie pan.
Press crushed Fritos into dough.
Brown hamburger in skillet; drain fat. Mix taco seasoning and tomato sauce into meat.
Top meat with sour cream.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° approximately 1/2 hour or until crust is brown.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Make Jell-O as directed on box.
Put in fruit and cool to set.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Melt and cool chocolate completely.
Add 1 egg at a time mixing on medium speed for 3 minutes following each egg.
Add vanilla and pour into pie shell.
I use a chocolate graham cracker crust and garnish the top with shaved Hershey bar.

title: nutty cole slaw
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seed in a little margarine.
Mix cabbage and onion in a large bowl.
When almonds and sesame seed are cool, mix with cabbage, onions and noodles.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in lard until like meal, then add water.
Press into ball and roll about 1/4-inch thick. Handle as little as possible.
Makes 2 crusts. Put in pie pan and bake at 450° until well browned.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Add one at a time the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Mash with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: snow peaked meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt. Shape firmly into loaf (8 x 4-inch). Place on shallow baking pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Frost with potatoes and sprinkle with cheese. Bake 15 minutes more. Blend remaining soup, water and 2 tablespoons drippings. Heat; stir occasionally. Serve with loaf. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread mixes as directed.
Cool and crumble.
Fry bacon until crispy.
Cool and crumble.
Dice tomato, onions and bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Chill 2 hours and serve.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Boil chicken until done; remove breasts.
Chill broth and remove fat.
Cook noodles in broth.
Add salt and garlic powder while cooking over medium heat.
Lower heat and add dry dip mix; cook until thick.
Remove; add sour cream and dressing.
Can be eaten cold or hot.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Combine onions and oil in skillet.
Cook on high for 3 or 4 minutes; whisk in flour.
When this starts to brown, add tomatoes. Stir until it thickens.
Add broth slowly, stirring constantly. Cook until desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper.

title: old fashioned dried apple custard
directions: In mixing bowl combine the apples, egg yolks, flour, sugar, milk, vanilla, butter and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted into center of custard.
Remove from oven and top with meringue.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Whip milk which has been chilled.
Gradually add sugar and lemon juice; pour into crust.
Freeze.
Cut into squares and eat.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together overnight and drain.
Put meat in the oven at 350 until dried out.
Can save the marinade for another batch.

title: reba's baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients
and bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve:
Use 1/2 cup mix with 8 ounces boiling water.
Top with marshmallows if you wish.

title: lemonade
directions: Combine the lemon juice, sugar and water.
Stir to mix well and dissolve all the sugar.
Add the lemon slices and chill well.

title: german sauerbraten
directions: Combine salt and ginger; rub over roast.
Place in a deep glass bowl.

title: spring chicken soup
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions and set aside. In a medium sized bowl, combine macaroni and broth, soup and milk. Set aside. In a large soup pot, saute ham, onion, carrots and celery in the butter. Add broth mixture and simmer over medium-low heat for 10 minutes. Stir in the tomatoes, chicken and seasoning. Add half and half and gently heat through. Serves 8 to 10.

title: asparagus and chicken quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry. Sprinkle chicken, asparagus, onion and cheese (in that order) in pastry lined pie plate. Beat eggs slightly. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie plate. Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, about 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Serves 6.

title: spaghetti pasta salad(tangy)
directions: You may use any vegetables as a substitute (chopped broccoli, cauliflower, etc.)

title: strawberry tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, rind and milk or cream. Cream until whipped cream consistency.
Fill tart shells.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: fruit and nut morning buns
directions: In large bowl combine hot roll mix, yeast packet, oats, flour, sugar, fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Add cream cheese, margarine, orange peel and egg.
Mix.
Add water.
Mix until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn dough out on floured surface.
Knead 5 minutes.
Shape dough in ball.
Cover.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Cut in half.
Cut each half into 6 pieces.
Shape each piece in ball. Place on cookie sheet.
Brush tops with melted margarine. Sprinkle with oats. Cover loosely.
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes. Heat oven to 375°.
Bake uncovered 26 to 28 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool.

title: fried rice
directions: In cooking oil, place onion and rice until slightly brown. Spray the casserole dish with Pam and other spray.
Combine drained mushrooms and cans of consomme.
Stir to blend.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Pour oil in baking pan.
Heat in a 350° oven.
Dip fish in beaten egg, then in cracker crumbs and arrange in preheated baking dish.
Bake until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: beef rice bake
directions: Brown beef and onion in pan. Add rice, soup, water, salt, celery and pepper. Mix well and put in baking dish. Cover and bake in 325 degree oven for one hour. Near end of baking time uncover, stir and top with potatoes chips. Finish baking.

title: award winning cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except walnuts) well.
Form into a ball shape.
Roll in walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Heat oleo, cocoa and water to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in salt, sugar, flour, eggs and sour cream.
Put on large greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.
Cool. Frost with icing.

title: candied shredded wheat
directions: Put biscuits in pie pan, pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Spread butter or margarine on top of each biscuit.
Put brown sugar over butter or margarine and melt both into biscuit with a small amount of hot water.
Cover with foil and place on stove burner or in oven until well steamed, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Kids love them and so do I.

title: cole slaw with vinegar dressing
directions: In saucepan, combine oil, sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add celery seed, mustard, salt and pepper.
Cool and store in jar.
Shake well and add to remaining ingredients to serve.

title: kraut dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, egg and cold water well and drop by teaspoons into boiling seasoned kraut.
Cover.
Turn heat to low and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cut apples in eighths and arrange on top of batter.
Melt 4 tablespoons oleo and pour over top of apples.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over apples.
Nuts are optional.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While still warm, string a glaze of powdered sugar and water over top.
Good with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken squash casserole
directions: Stir-fry squash and onion; fold in carrots, peas and chicken. Combine sour cream and soup.
Combine croutons and butter. Spread half of crouton mix into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour chicken and vegetables on top of croutons, then add the sour cream and soup mix.
Top with remaining croutons.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine egg, sugar, mustard, vinegar, salt and grated onion in blender; process one minute.
With motor still running, pour oil into mixture in a slow, steady stream.
Pour into a bowl; stir in poppy seed.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Place chocolate in top of double boiler. Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cook until chocolate melts.
Combine the cream cheese and sugar. Beat until smooth. Add chocolate and vanilla, beating well.
Stir in chopped pecans. Press mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.
Top each square with a pecan half. Store in refrigerator.
Yields 16 squares.

title: sweet barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine beef, milk, oatmeal, crumbs, eggs, 1/2 cup onion, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Mixture will be soft; shape into walnut-sized balls.
Place in a large baking pan.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake cake mix according to package directions in 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Cut each layer in half horizontally to make a total of 4 layers.
Mix together the coconut, sour cream, vanilla and whipped topping.
Spread mixture between layers on sides and on top.
Refrigerate.
This cake gets better with age.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk.
Add coconut and form into blocks.
Refrigerate for about 1 1/2 hours.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate and wax.
Dip blocks into chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.

title: chicken, peas, nut salad
directions: Prepare each of the items separately, then mix together with the dressing:

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Mix together egg, vinegar and water.
Add 8 tablespoons of liquid to dry ingredients, mixing lightly with fork.
Roll crust between two pieces of wax paper or plastic wrap. Makes 2 crusts.
Can be stored in refrigerator or freezer.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together in buttered casserole.
Store overnight in refrigerator.
Take out of refrigerator one hour before baking. Top with crushed potato chips before baking.
Bake 49 minutes at 350°.
Very good.
Serves 10.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine ingredients in glass dish like pie pan.
Break up butter and cook at highest microwave power for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and stir.
Then add peanut butter (to taste) and nuts (if desired).
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Keep refrigerated.

title: green beans with marjoram
directions: Wash green beans. Trim ends and remove strings. Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Bring 3/4 cup water to a boil in a Dutch oven. Add green beans. Cover. Reduce heat to medium and cook 8 minutes, stirring frequently. Drain. Return beans to pan. Add butter and remaining ingredients. Cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring often. Yield: 6 servings.

title: amaretti cookies
directions: Pre-heat oven to 325°.
Line cookie sheet with parchment paper or fitted brown bag.
Blend ingredients by hand or use food processor.
Break almond paste in pieces.
Gradually blend in sugars, flour, salt and egg white.

Using two teaspoons, drop heaping teaspoonful on paper; swirl into oval shape, peaking upwards. Decorate with 4 to 8 nuts (place firmly into dough) and/or press cherry into center of cookie and press pignoli nuts (pine nuts) around cherry.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together with spoon until sugar is dissolved. Combine dry ingredients; add to oil/sugar mixture.
Add eggs (one at a time), stirring well after each egg.
Add vanilla, chopped pecans, chopped apples and coconut.
Batter will be thick. Pour into tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour and fifteen minutes.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine and mix until creamy the Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Pour cheese mixture over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Cool completely and sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Refrigerate.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples; cut into fourths. Unroll and separate crescent rolls. Wrap each piece of apple in one crescent roll. Place in 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Combine margarine, sugar and orange juice in saucepan; bring to a boil and remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Pour over rolls; bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Spoon pan juice over rolls when serving.

title: italian nut rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine ingredients, except for flour.
Mix on medium speed for one minute.
Gradually add flour.
Roll dough into one-inch balls.
Roll into egg whites, then nuts.

title: jane's butter pecan muffins
directions: Mix flour, pecans and brown sugar together. Beat egg, milk, butter and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients. Fill muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Mix and chill 2 hours.
Roll on floured board quite thick.
Cut and place raisin and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.

title: pork chops with sour cream gravy
directions: Brown mushrooms in butter; remove.
Brown chops on both sides and season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup water, Worcestershire and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Remove chops and keep warm.
Mix flour and remaining water and stir into liquid in skillet.
Cook until thick.
Simmer 5 minutes. Stir in sour cream and pour over chops.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: country fried steak and cream gravy
directions: Pound round steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle steaks with 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and garlic salt.
Dredge steak in 1/2 cup flour and dip in 1/2 cup milk.
Return to flour and dredge again.
Brown steaks in hot oil in a large skillet.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.
Set aside.

title: sausage-cheese pinwheels
directions: Mix biscuit
dough
(Bisquick may be used).
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick
into rectangular pieces, about 10-inches wide. Brush with melted
butter
and sprinkle with grated cheese and sausage.
Roll as
for
jelly
roll
and cut in 1-inch slices. Place flat on greased
baking
sheets
and bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Delicious!

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and butter; beat in sugar and vanilla.

title: kielbasa with kraut
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onions and bacon until tender but not browned.
Take off fat.
Stir in beer.
Combine water with cornstarch, brown mustard, molasses, caraway seed, allspice and pepper.
Stir into bacon mixture; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add rutabaga; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir in kielbasa, apples and sauerkraut.
Cook covered 15 to 20 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: 1-2-3 biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl mix the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the milk and oil all at once.
Stir until dough forms into a ball.
Hand knead in bowl 10 times to smooth. Roll dough between 2 sheets of waxed paper to a 6-inch square (about 1-inch thick).
Cut into 9-square biscuits.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 9 biscuits.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans on bottom of well-greased Bundt pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Layer in pan.
May be refrigerated overnight at this stage.
Then pour mixture over just before baking.

title: butterflied leg of lamb
directions: Put lamb, fat side down, in shallow pan.
Combine all seasonings together and pour marinade over lamb.
Cover tightly; refrigerate overnight.
Turn meat at least once.
Take lamb out of refrigerator 1 hour before cooking it.
Make incisions to meat to lay flat.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 10 minutes.
Turn, baste and broil 10 minutes on other side.
Lower temperature to 425° for 15 minutes.
Test with a sharp knife.
Meat should be pink and juicy.
Carve into thin slices to serve.
This is great grilled outside.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms and remove stems.
Mix next 5 ingredients, then toss with crabmeat.
Fill each mushroom crown with mixture.
Bake at 375° until hot, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: If not thick enough, thicken with perma flo.
Add cheese, nuts, pineapple, whipped cream or Rich's topping when cooled.

title: old fashion banana
directions: Layer in an 8 x 10-inch pie dish, bananas and then wafers until 2 inches from top of dish.
Mix eggs, vanilla, milk and sugar together in a small pot.
Heat until boils; pour over layers of bananas and wafers.
Preheat oven at 375° and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mocha creamer
directions: Combine all ingredients in a container with a tight fitting lid.
Shake well to blend.
Store in an airtight container.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Blend together vegetable oil, sugar and eggs, then add buttermilk, salt, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add to the other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cream sherbet
directions: Make a very sweet lemonade, then add a small can of grated pineapple.
Put this in a freezer, the same as for ice cream, and turn. When the lemonade begins to thicken, add a pint of sweetened cream and freeze as hard as you wish it.
This makes 3 quarts.

title: eggplant salad(melitzanosalata; serves six)
directions: *Tomato can be substituted by 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Place flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, margarine, egg and milk in a bowl and beat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Place in greased pie pan and shape over bottom and up the sides to the top.
Drain peaches and reserve 3 tablespoons of the syrup.
Pour peaches into pie crust.

title: vegetable beef casserole
directions: In a 3-quart casserole layer half of the potatoes, carrots, celery, green beans and onion.
Crumble half of the uncooked beef over vegetables.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon each of thyme, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Top with tomatoes.
Cover and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake about 1 hour longer or until vegetables are tender and meat is done.
Sprinkle with cheese, cover and let stand until cheese is melted.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Take aluminum foil and put 1 patty on it and slice onion and potatoes and carrots.
Put some butter on top and add seasoning. Do this until amount of patties as desired or needed.
Cook in a 350° oven for about an hour and half.
Enjoy!

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix all the seasonings with the flour.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Dip chicken in milk batter, then in seasoned flour and frie in hot oil for 15 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift together corn meal, flour, sugar and salt.
Add egg, milk and oil; beat with wire beater until smooth.
Bake in greased pan for 20 minutes in a preheated oven at 425°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into bite sizes.
Chop apple, slice grapes, add to chicken.
Add salt and pepper; add mayonnaise to desired consistency.

title: chili mac
directions: Saute onion until clear.
Add mango and turn down low.
Fry ground beef.
Drain.
Add salt and chili powder.
Then add onions and mango mixture.
Mix. Toss cooked macaroni, tomatoes and chili into this.
Mix well.
Pour into a casserole, laying and lapping the cheese on top.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes in a 300° oven. Substitute:
1 can tomato puree and 1 can of whole tomatoes for the 4 cups of tomatoes.
